{"type":"message","id":"258fb9b9","parentId":"edc5b75f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:18:21.992Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There are Spark-related memory files. Let me read the relevant ones to understand what Spark is and what the setup looks like.","thinkingSignature":"2fe6138c475c5ae02016c999c56809b6fac9ae1bc1c4b19acf75d081aaf6e083"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t0s4tnb54h0w_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-23-modal-ollama-spark.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t0s4tnb54h0w_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-23-spark-persona-plan.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":7543,"output":123,"cacheRead":13714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21380,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774275498593}}
{"type":"message","id":"d8f5fa13","parentId":"258fb9b9","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:18:22.116Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_t0s4tnb54h0w_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session: 2026-03-23 14:13:24 UTC\n\n- **Session Key**: agent:main:main\n- **Session ID**: 5f5a5e23-20f6-4246-93c6-323d032bbab4\n- **Source**: webchat\n\n## Conversation Summary\n\nassistant: Zero machines in the account. The old Paperspace notebook is gone and the API key only has list/get permissions — can't create new machines without template IDs we can't fetch. \n\nThe path forward: Modal.com has a free tier + A100s, and they have a clean REST API. Let me check if Zach has an account there, or we could just use Lambda Labs. Either would give us a public Ollama endpoint in like 5 minutes.\n\nWant me to set up Modal as the GPU backend for SPARK?\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-23 10:01 EDT] sure i signed up for it\nassistant: Modal is authenticated — zero apps, ready to go. Let me write the Ollama GPU endpoint on Modal.\n\nassistant: Credentials are ready. Now I'll write the Modal app that runs Ollama with an A100 GPU.\n\nassistant: Let me rewrite with the correct Modal decorator pattern — `@build()` and `@enter()` need to be separate methods.\n\nassistant: Actually, let me simplify — let Ollama auto-pull the model on first request. No explicit pull needed.\n\nassistant: Now let's deploy it.\n\nassistant: Two quick fixes — `curl` isn't in debian_slim, and FastAPI needs to be explicit.\n\nassistant: Build succeeded — the error is in Modal's internal runner trying to print unicode (checkmark from pip install). Let me retry.\n\nassistant: Need `zstd` for Ollama's installer. Quick fix.\n\nassistant: Deployed! Let me test the endpoint and then wire it into SPARK.\n\nassistant: Both endpoints mapped to the same URL — need distinct paths. Quick fix.\n\nassistant: Both endpoints deployed with distinct URLs. Let me test and then wire SPARK to use it.\n\nassistant: Health check passes. Now let me test generate — first request cold-starts the container and pulls the model (~30s).\n\nassistant: Container still starting up (model pull in progress). Let me poll until ready.\n\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774275502077}}
{"type":"message","id":"0cc73426","parentId":"d8f5fa13","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:18:22.158Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_t0s4tnb54h0w_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session: 2026-03-23 05:08:05 UTC\n\n- **Session Key**: agent:main:main\n- **Session ID**: 0c88e81c-65d2-4b7b-bd9f-989606505278\n- **Source**: webchat\n\n## Conversation Summary\n\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-23 00:36 EDT] what already exists on openclaw hub like this?\nassistant: <final>\nFound it. Here's what's already on ClawHub:\n\n**`open-persona`** (NeilJo-GY, v0.19.1) — closest to what you're thinking. Meta-skill for building and managing persona packs. Has architecture docs, presets, evolution system. Looks fairly mature.\n\n**`personality-switcher`** (Robb1010, v0.1.3) — `/personality` command to switch between saved personas, `/create-personality` to design new ones. Persists across sessions, has rollback safeguards. Simpler than open-persona.\n\n**`persona-voice`** (Hei-MaoM) — Chinese market, Feishu/Lark bot integration, TTS voice output. Not relevant to your thing.\n\n**What they all have in common:** They're essentially static persona templates — you pick one, it loads a SOUL.md/IDENTITY.md, that's the personality. None of them do **context-reactive trait propagation** based on the conversation content. That's the gap in the market. What you've built — signal-based trait detection + SPARK emotional engine + hysteresis — is genuinely different from what's already there.\n\nThe differentiator isn't the persona presets. It's that the personality *responds to what you're saying*. If I were building a shop around this, that's the demo I'd lead with.\n</final>\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-23 00:40 EDT] yeah lets try and do it. Maybe take a look at all of my projects and spin up a couple plans for the best ideas you can come up with. use spark if you can to really brainstorm hard and also search the openclaw hub for similar products to make sure the spot isnt already taken.\nassistant: Now let me hit SPARK for the real brainstorm:\n\nassistant: Now let me look at what ClawHub has that is closest — `agent-soul-crafter` and `open-persona`:\n\nassistant: <final>\nOkay. Here's the full picture.\n\n**The market gap is real, and it's large.** Everything on ClawHub for \"personality\" is static:\n\n| Product | What it does | Limitation |\n|---------|-------------|-------------|\n| `agent-soul-crafter` | Builds SOUL.md templates | Static forever |\n| `open-persona` | Framework for persona packs | Framework only, no reactive layer |\n| `personality-switcher` | Swaps between static presets | Same problem — no context response |\n| `aura` | HEXACO questionnaire → config | Fixed at design time |\n| `neokarma-soulmd-builder` | Persistent personality | Evolves with conversation, not with *tone* |\n| `personality` (DISC) | Human communication styles | Not an agent personality system |\n\nThe entire competitive landscape is template-based. None of them have what you built: **signal-based trait propagation + SPARK emotional engine + hysteresis**. The personality actually responds to what you're saying, in real-time, every turn. That's genuinely novel in this space.\n\n**Three plans, in order of speed-to-revenue:**\n\n---\n\n**Plan 1 — ClawHub Skill (\"living-persona\") — Fastest**\n*Days to ship, $0 to start*\n\nPackage the hook + persona.py + SPARK as a ClawHub skill. Free tier: signal analyzer + basic trait propagation. Paid tier ($5-15/mo): SPARK integration, premium preset packs, hysteresis tuning. You become the alternative to static personality systems — and there are a lot of OpenClaw users who want this.\n\n*Upside:* Instant distribution via ClawHub. Zero infrastructure.\n*Downside:* Low price ceiling, easy to fork.\n\n---\n\n**Plan 2 — SaaS Product (\"PersonaForge\" or \"AgentVoice\") — Core product**\n*Weeks to ship, recurring revenue*\n\nWeb dashboard where users:\n- Pick a base archetype (therapist, coder, writer, sage, etc.)\n- Adjust trait sliders with live preview\n- See the personality respond to sample conversations in real-time\n- Export to ClawHub OR connect via API\n\nThe **preview debugger** is the core differentiator. Every competitor sells you a static description of a personality. You sell them a *living personality they can stress-test before installing*. That's a meaningfully better buying experience.\n\n*Monetization:* $10-49/mo subscriptions, lifetime license option.\n*Upside:* Real SaaS, real recurring revenue, defensible UX moat.\n*Downside:* Needs a web UI + hosting.\n\n---\n\n**Plan 3 — Platform (\"AgentSouls\") — Network effects, biggest)*\n*Months to build, highest ceiling*\n\nB2B: License the SPARK emotional engine as an API to AI agent platform builders. \"Give your agents emotional intelligence\" — SPARK maps tensions/modes to behavioral signatures.\n\nCreators: Build and sell personality presets. You take a cut. Like WordPress themes, but for AI agents.\n\nThe ClawHub data + your existing agent infrastructure (selfhelper, breakaway, etc.) could seed this with real products fast.\n\n*Upside:* Platform economics, network effects, B2B contracts are large.\n*Downside:* Requires real sales motion, not just a listing.\n\n---\n\n**My honest recommendation:** Ship Plan 1 immediately — it's code you already have. Simultaneously build the Plan 2 preview engine, because that's what makes the concept *real* to buyers. They're not buying a personality system; they're buying a personality system they can see working before they trust it.\n\nWant me to start scaffolding Plan 1 (the ClawHub skill)?\n</final>\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-23 00:47 EDT] lets do it\nassistant: Now building the skill — SKILL.md, the structural hook, signal engine, and presets all at once:\n\nassistant: Now the presets and setup docs:\n\nassistant: Now let's install and test it:\n\nuser: Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-03-23 01:00 EDT] keep going nova <3\nassistant: Gateway is back. Let me test the hook end-to-end:\n\nassistant: Files are live. Let me check what got written:\n\nassistant: Hook is working perfectly. The structural directive fires: **\"candid, direct\"** — exactly right for a frustrated developer message. The trait state shows proper propagation and residual decay is tracking.\n\nNow let me package and publish:\n\nassistant: <final>\nIt's built, installed, and tested. Here's what's live:\n\n**Hook installed:** `living-persona` is in `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\hooks\\living-persona\\` and enabled.\n\n**Tested and working:**\n- Incoming: *\"frustrated with this python code...\"*  \n- Output: `[Voice directive] Active traits: candid, direct.` — proper structural injection\n\n**Files:**\n```\nliving-persona/\n├── SKILL.md           — skill description + usage\n├── HOOK.md            — hook documentation\n├── hook.json          — config (structural mode, hysteresis tuned)\n├── handler.ts         — the full personality engine (JS, runs in gateway process)\n├── references/\n│   ├── presets.md     — 7 presets: nova, cynic, sage, coach, ghost, hacker, romantic\n│   └── setup.md       — installation guide\n└── scripts/\n    └── reset_persona.py — reset trait state on /new\n```\n\n**To publish to ClawHub** — I need your login token:\n```bash\nclawhub login --token <your-token>\n```\nThen I can run `clawhub publish ./living-persona`. After that it's live on the marketplace.\n\n**Also:** the SPARK integration isn't wired into the TypeScript handler yet — the Python version has it, the JS port doesn't (no Python interpreter in the gateway process). That's the last piece if you want SPARK emotional engine in the structural layer too.\n</final>\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774275502116}}
