{"type":"message","id":"4f4b1853","parentId":"f9be2e7a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:18:59.562Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_j6boilcdd0ni_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[32;1mName[0m\r\n[32;1m----[0m\r\nmodal_ollama.py\r\nspark_app.py\r\n__init__.py\r\nmain.py"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1437,"aggregated":"[32;1mName[0m\r\n[32;1m----[0m\r\nmodal_ollama.py\r\nspark_app.py\r\n__init__.py\r\nmain.py","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774275539527}}
{"type":"message","id":"c2078642","parentId":"4f4b1853","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:19:02.177Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the Modal deployment file to see what GPU is being used.","thinkingSignature":"7b9a9090497db88a7f23b300b6341939c10f8fe3dcc50ff8299a35c9c4808637"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ihtvxxs2k8ni_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\deploy\\modal_ollama.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":12026,"output":62,"cacheRead":13714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25802,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774275539563}}
{"type":"message","id":"fb085db3","parentId":"c2078642","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:19:02.253Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ihtvxxs2k8ni_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nSPARK Ollama GPU endpoint on Modal\nDeploy: modal deploy spark.deploy.modal_ollama\nEndpoint: https://spark-ollama-qwen-{user}.modal.run\n\"\"\"\n\nimport modal\n\napp = modal.App(\"spark-ollama\")\n\nollama_image = (\n    modal.Image.debian_slim(python_version=\"3.11\")\n    .pip_install(\"requests\", \"httpx\", \"fastapi[standard]\")\n    .run_commands(\n        \"apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl zstd && curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\",\n    )\n    .env({\"OLLAMA_MODELS\": \"/root/.ollama\"})\n)\n\n\n@app.cls(\n    image=ollama_image,\n    gpu=\"A100\",\n    memory=32768,\n    scaledown_window=600,\n    timeout=3600,\n)\nclass OllamaEndpoint:\n    \"\"\"\n    Ollama on A100 GPU. Model auto-pulls on first generate request (~30s cold start).\n    After that, subsequent requests are fast.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    @modal.enter()\n    def start_server(self):\n        import subprocess, os, signal, sys\n\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] Starting ollama serve...\", file=sys.stderr)\n        self._process = subprocess.Popen(\n            [\"ollama\", \"serve\"],\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n            preexec_fn=os.setsid,\n        )\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] ollama serve started, pid=\", self._process.pid, file=sys.stderr)\n\n    @modal.exit()\n    def stop_server(self):\n        import os, signal, sys\n\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] Shutting down...\", file=sys.stderr)\n        try:\n            os.killpg(os.getpgid(self._process.pid), signal.SIGTERM)\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n\n    @modal.fastapi_endpoint(label=\"spark-ollama-qwen-generate\")\n    def generate(self, body: dict):\n        \"\"\"\n        body: { prompt: str, model?: str = \"qwen2.5:7b\", options?: { temperature?, num_predict? } }\n        \"\"\"\n        import requests\n\n        payload = {\n            \"model\": body.get(\"model\", \"qwen2.5:7b\"),\n            \"prompt\": body.get(\"prompt\", \"\"),\n            \"stream\": False,\n            \"options\": body.get(\"options\", {}),\n        }\n        resp = requests.post(\n            \"http://localhost:11434/api/generate\",\n            json=payload,\n            timeout=120,\n        )\n        resp.raise_for_status()\n        return {\"response\": resp.json().get(\"response\", \"\"), \"model\": payload[\"model\"]}\n\n    @modal.fastapi_endpoint(label=\"spark-ollama-qwen-health\")\n    def health(self):\n        return {\"status\": \"ok\", \"service\": \"spark-ollama\", \"model\": \"qwen2.5:7b\"}\n\n\n@app.local_entrypoint()\ndef test():\n    print(\"spark-ollama module loaded OK\")\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774275542216}}
{"type":"message","id":"276a1796","parentId":"fb085db3","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:19:24.594Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, so Spark's Modal endpoint is using:\n- **GPU: A100** (40GB or 80GB variant)\n- **Memory: 32768 MB (32GB)**\n- **Model: qwen2.5:7b** (a 7B parameter model)\n\nZach's questions:\n\n1. **\"open a ui for spark in model\"** - I think he wants to add Spark as a model/provider in OpenClaw's `models.json` so it shows up in the model picker UI. This would mean adding it as an Ollama-style provider pointing to the Modal endpoint.\n\n2. **\"make sure its uncensored\"** - Ollama has no built-in content filtering - it's just running the model. The \"censorship\" would come from the model itself (Qwen has some built-in). To make it truly uncensored, you'd want to use a model that's been unfiltered (like various fine-tuned models). Options:\n   - `mistral-nemo` or other uncensored fine-tuned models\n   - Use a model with system prompt override to remove any safety training\n\n3. **\"do we have to use an a100? its expensive\"** - For a 7B model like Qwen 2.5, a 7B or 14B parameter model runs easily on much cheaper options. An A100 at ~$2-3/hr is overkill when a A5000 (~$0.50-0.70/hr) or even a T4 (~$0.30/hr) would handle it fine. The A100 only makes sense if they're running something much larger.\n\nNow I need to figure out what Zach means by \"open a ui for spark in model\" - he probably wants to integrate Spark into OpenClaw's model UI. Let me think through the GPU options for a 7B model: A5000 is available on Modal and would be significantly cheaper than A100, though it depends on what Modal actually offers in their GPU lineup.\n\nActually, thinking about this more practically - if Spark is Zach's creative writing project, the Modal endpoint is the backend running the Ollama instance, and he wants it accessible as a model in OpenClaw's model picker. The uncensored part likely means he wants to use a model that doesn't have safety filtering built in, like Qwen 2.5 or a similar 7B model.\n\nFor the GPU, Modal's free tier doesn't include GPU access, but they do offer T4 GPUs at competitive rates - I should clarify what the actual hourly costs are and whether there's a better GPU option for his use case.","thinkingSignature":"a3eb11dca9878a3c76c9bd99b4f7ac2359bc853da3252f7c43117a6ababc97f0"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it. Found it — `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark/deploy/modal_ollama.py`. A few things to address:\n\n**GPU:** Currently hardcoded to `A100` with 32GB memory. For a **7B model (qwen2.5:7b)**, this is massive overkill and expensive. A **T4** (16GB, ~$0.30/hr) or **A10G** (24GB, ~$0.50/hr) would run it fine. A100 is 5-10x the cost for zero benefit at this model size. Want me to change it to A5000 or T4?\n\n**Uncensored:** Ollama itself has no filter — the filtering comes from the model. Qwen2.5 has some baked-in safety. For truly unfiltered, you'd want something like a fine-tuned uncensored variant (e.g., `mistral-nemo-instruct-uncensored` or a custom fine-tune). What's the actual use case — creative writing, roleplay, something else?\n\n**\"UI for Spark in model\":** I'm guessing you want Spark's Modal endpoint added to OpenClaw's `models.json` as an Ollama provider so it appears in the model picker? That would mean pointing an Ollama provider at `https://spark-ollama-qwen-{user}.modal.run`. Can you confirm that's what you want?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":12749,"output":846,"cacheRead":13714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27309,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774275542256}}
