{"type":"message","id":"3ee0e1a0","parentId":"e6a4dd29","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:23:58.797Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to add a new Ollama provider for the Modal endpoint. The Modal endpoint is at `https://toxzak-svg--spark-ollama-qwen-generate.modal.run`. \n\nBut wait - OpenClaw's Ollama integration expects the Ollama API format at `http://host:11434/api/generate`. The Modal endpoint is a FastAPI endpoint that accepts `{prompt, model, options}` and returns `{response, model}`. This is similar to Ollama's API but not exactly the same format.\n\nLooking at the Modal generate endpoint, the request format is:\n```json\n{ \"prompt\": \"...\", \"model\": \"qwen2.5:7b\", \"options\": {} }\n\n\n```\n\nAnd the response is:\n```json\n{ \"response\": \"...\", \"model\": \"qwen2.5:7b\" }\n```\n\nOllama's standard `/api/generate` endpoint takes the same request shape and returns a response with `response`, `model`, plus additional fields like `done` and timing info. The Modal endpoint is close enough that I could add a new Ollama provider pointing to it, but the `apiKey` field would need to be set to something appropriate since Modal doesn't use Ollama's authentication format.\n\nActually, OpenClaw should be able to work with this as long as I configure the base URL correctly and accept the default `ollama` API type, even though the API response format might differ slightly from standard Ollama.\n\n```\nI'm checking the Ollama API specification more carefully - the Modal endpoint at `/generate` matches the standard Ollama format exactly with model, prompt, stream, and options fields, so it should be compatible. I'll configure it as a new Ollama provider with the base URL pointing to the Modal endpoint and set apiKey to \"modal\" since that's what OpenClaw expects for Ollama providers.\n```","thinkingSignature":"4fc88156db6927df899c010cabf666405f9b6bc98913b66abed1bb68885929ec"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1pez