{"type":"message","id":"bfee8a23","parentId":"67d4bbab","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:25:15.534Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, getting \"Method Not Allowed\" on the generate endpoint. This might be because the FastAPI endpoint is mounted at a specific path. The Modal app has two endpoints:\n- `spark-ollama-qwen-health` \n- `spark-ollama-qwen-generate`\n\nThese are separate endpoints with different labels. But the base URL for the generate endpoint is `https://toxzak-svg--spark-ollama-qwen-generate.modal.run`. Maybe the FastAPI is responding at the root path but the actual POST needs to go to a specific path like `/generate`.\n\nWait, looking at the Modal app again - it has two `@modal.fastapi_endpoint` decorators with different labels. \n\nSo the health endpoint is at `https://toxzak-svg--spark-ollama-qwen-health.modal.run` and the generate endpoint is at `https://toxzak-svg--spark-ollama-qwen-generate.modal.run`. Since these are separate endpoints with distinct labels, each should be accessible at its own root path. Let me check the Modal logs to see if there's an issue, or try curling the endpoint directly.","thinkingSignature":"88a8b2ad173831b2630995ba1ed5a9091662d091b4867787d895aa5372469596"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3hj9ysii302d_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST \"https://toxzak-svg--spark-ollama-qwen-generate.modal.run\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d \"{\\\"prompt\\\":\\\"Say hello\\\",\\\"model\\\":\\\"qwen2.5:7b\\\"}\" 2>&1","yieldMs":35000,"timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":23044,"output":336,"cacheRead":13714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37094,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774275906561}}
