(duration: 147.1 ms, execution: 23.6 ms)\r\n    GET / -> 200 OK  (duration: 117.8 ms, execution: 17.4 ms)\r\n    GET / -> 200 OK  (duration: 136.9 ms, execution: 22.3 ms)\r\n    GET / -> 200 OK  (duration: 151.8 ms, execution: 19.7 ms)\r\n    GET / -> 200 OK  (duration: 188.5 ms, execution: 42.2 ms)\r\n    GET / -> 200 OK  (duration: 104.0 ms, execution: 17.9 ms)\r\n    GET / -> 200 OK  (duration: 199.4 ms, execution: 35.2 ms)\r\n    GET /favicon.ico -> 404 Not Found  (duration: 253.3 ms, execution: 17.4 ms)\r\n    GET / -> 405 Method Not Allowed  (duration: 284.3 ms, execution: 19.1 ms)\r\n[spark-ollama] Shutting down...\r\n[spark-ollama] Starting ollama serve...\r\n[spark-ollama] ollama serve started, pid= 4\r\n    GET / -> 200 OK  (duration: 5.91 s, execution: 125.5 ms)\r\n   POST / -> 405 Method Not Allowed  (duration: 149.6 ms, execution: 61.2 ms)\r\n   POST / -> 405 Method Not Allowed  (duration: 121.8 ms, execution: 42.7 ms)\r\n   POST / -> 405 Method Not Allowed  (duration: 152.7 ms, execution: 16.7 ms)\r\n    GET / -> 200 OK  (duration: 109.1 ms, execution: 23.7 ms)\r\n   POST / -> 405 Method Not Allowed  (duration: 149.9 ms, execution: 28.1 ms)\r\n   POST /generate -> 404 Not Found  (duration: 164.1 ms, execution: 37.9 ms)\r\n    GET /openapi.json -> 404 Not Found  (duration: 118.9 ms, execution: 32.2 ms)\r\n    GET /openapi.json -> 404 Not Found  (duration: 106.7 ms, execution: 37.2 ms)\r\n","name":"modal app"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774276050781}}
{"type":"message","id":"d0670830","parentId":"32798b9d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:27:59.929Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the problem now! The logs reveal two critical issues:\n\n1. **`POST / -> 405 Method Not Allowed`** - The FastAPI endpoint doesn't accept POST at the root `/`. This means the `fastapi_endpoint` decorator doesn't expose class methods the way I expected.\n\n2. **`ollama serve` IS running** - the logs show `[spark-ollama] Starting ollama serve...` and `ollama serve started, pid= 4`. So Ollama is running.\n\n3. **`404 Client Error: Not Found for url: http://localhost:11434/api/generate`** - This is the real problem! The first POST attempt actually got through to the generate handler, but `ollama serve` returned 404. This means:\n\n\nThe endpoint is responding to requests, but Ollama itself isn't recognizing the `/api/generate` route. I think the issue is that `ollama serve` is the command I should be using, not `ollama run`, and the server might not be exposing the endpoints I expect by default.\n\nLooking at the actual error more carefully—the 405 Method Not Allowed suggests the FastAPI route exists but the HTTP method isn't allowed, which means POST requests to `/` aren't being routed to the handler. This could be because the decorator isn't exposing the method correctly, or there's a path mismatch between where the route is registered and where I'm trying to call it.\n\nThe original deployment actually worked with A100, so this might be a cold start issue where the model hasn't finished pulling yet. The 404 from Ollama's API suggests the model isn't ready—the error points to `http://localhost:11434/api/generate` not being available, which means either Ollama hasn't fully started or the model pull timed out during the cold start phase.\n\nLooking at the timing, a 5.91 second startup followed immediately by a 405 error suggests the container just came up and Ollama might still be initializing. I should wait longer before attempting the first request to give Ollama time to fully load.\n\nBut the 405 error is puzzling—that's FastAPI saying the route exists but the method isn't allowed, which doesn't make sense if the endpoint is defined as accepting POST. Let me reconsider how Modal's `fastapi_endpoint` decorator actually exposes class methods, since there might be something about the API design I'm missing.\n\nLooking back at the logs though, the real issue surfaces in that 500 error: Ollama is returning a 404 when the container tries to reach `http://localhost:11434/api/generate`. The Ollama server is running, but it doesn't have that endpoint available—likely because the model hasn't been pulled yet or isn't loaded. The 405 I'm seeing now could be a red herring, maybe from a second request hitting the endpoint before the model is ready.\n\nThe fix is straightforward: I need to add an endpoint to explicitly pull the model before trying to use it. Looking at Modal's documentation, the approach would be to use `ollama pull` during the container setup rather than relying on auto-pull, or add a dedicated pull endpoint that gets called once during initialization.\n\nThe real issue is that the generate endpoint is failing with a 404 from Ollama itself—the model probably hasn't finished downloading. Rather than trying to fix this through the code right now, I should just pull the model explicitly and verify it works. The class method approach with `self` might also be affecting how the endpoint is being called, so that's worth investigating separately.\n\nLooking at the actual deployment, the endpoint is returning 405 for POST requests, which suggests either a Modal routing issue or the container is still cold-starting. Since the health endpoint works fine, the FastAPI app itself is running—the 405 on POST to `/` indicates something specific about how that endpoint is configured. the old container. The 405 suggests the request IS reaching the endpoint, but POST isn't allowed there. Let me check the Modal docs more carefully—maybe `fastapi_endpoint` on a class method creates the endpoint at a specific path rather than `/`, and I need to hit that exact path instead.\n\nLooking at the logs, `/` returns 405 but `/generate` returns 404, which means `/` exists as a route but POST isn't permitted on it while `/generate` doesn't exist at all. This is confusing because the decorator should create the endpoint at `/`. I think I might be misunderstanding how `modal.fastapi_endpoint()` works with class methods, so let me just pull the model explicitly and test again to see if that resolves the underlying issue.","thinkingSignature":"bae2663572caa2fbab22330f40aa2029420b31f426d90d9d83753ab1ceda33f3"},{"type":"text","text":"Found the issue — Ollama's API returned 404: the model hasn't been pulled yet. Let me fix the Modal app to auto-pull on startup:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4svttke7e6mi_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\deploy\\modal_ollama.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":29435,"output":1004,"cacheRead":13714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44153,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774276050820}}
{"type":"message","id":"efbf8d79","parentId":"d0670830","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:27:59.992Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4svttke7e6mi_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nSPARK Ollama GPU endpoint on Modal\nDeploy: modal deploy spark.deploy.modal_ollama\nEndpoint: https://spark-ollama-qwen-{user}.modal.run\n\"\"\"\n\nimport modal\n\napp = modal.App(\"spark-ollama\")\n\nollama_image = (\n    modal.Image.debian_slim(python_version=\"3.11\")\n    .pip_install(\"requests\", \"httpx\", \"fastapi[standard]\")\n    .run_commands(\n        \"apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl zstd && curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\",\n    )\n    .env({\"OLLAMA_MODELS\": \"/root/.ollama\"})\n)\n\n\n@app.cls(\n    image=ollama_image,\n    gpu=\"T4\",  # cheapest GPU on Modal (~0.30/hr)\n    memory=16384,\n    scaledown_window=600,\n    timeout=3600,\n)\nclass OllamaEndpoint:\n    \"\"\"\n    Ollama on A100 GPU. Model auto-pulls on first generate request (~30s cold start).\n    After that, subsequent requests are fast.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    @modal.enter()\n    def start_server(self):\n        import subprocess, os, signal, sys\n\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] Starting ollama serve...\", file=sys.stderr)\n        self._process = subprocess.Popen(\n            [\"ollama\", \"serve\"],\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n            preexec_fn=os.setsid,\n        )\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] ollama serve started, pid=\", self._process.pid, file=sys.stderr)\n\n    @modal.exit()\n    def stop_server(self):\n        import os, signal, sys\n\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] Shutting down...\", file=sys.stderr)\n        try:\n            os.killpg(os.getpgid(self._process.pid), signal.SIGTERM)\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n\n    @modal.fastapi_endpoint(label=\"spark-ollama-qwen-generate\")\n    def generate(self, body: dict):\n        \"\"\"\n        body: { prompt: str, model?: str = \"qwen2.5:7b\", options?: { temperature?, num_predict? } }\n        \"\"\"\n        import requests\n\n        payload = {\n            \"model\": body.get(\"model\", \"qwen2.5:7b\"),\n            \"prompt\": body.get(\"prompt\", \"\"),\n            \"stream\": False,\n            \"options\": body.get(\"options\", {}),\n        }\n        resp = requests.post(\n            \"http://localhost:11434/api/generate\",\n            json=payload,\n            timeout=120,\n        )\n        resp.raise_for_status()\n        return {\"response\": resp.json().get(\"response\", \"\"), \"model\": payload[\"model\"]}\n\n    @modal.fastapi_endpoint(label=\"spark-ollama-qwen-health\")\n    def health(self):\n        return {\"status\": \"ok\", \"service\": \"spark-ollama\", \"model\": \"qwen2.5:7b\"}\n\n\n@app.local_entrypoint()\ndef test():\n    print(\"spark-ollama module loaded OK\")\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774276079963}}
{"type":"message","id":"21047f8d","parentId":"efbf8d79","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:28:15.218Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue now. The `start_server` just starts `ollama serve` but doesn't pull the model. The model needs to be pulled explicitly. Let me update `start_server` to pull the model before starting.\n\nAlso, I notice the docstring still says \"A100 GPU\" even though I changed to T4. Let me fix that.\n\nFor pulling the model, I should use `subprocess.run([\"ollama\", \"pull\", \"qwen2.5:7b\"], ...)` before starting the server or after. Actually, I should pull it in `start_server` before the `serve` command starts, or I can run it in a separate subprocess and wait for it to complete.\n\n\nI'll modify `start_server` to pull the model first, then start Ollama serve. The tricky part is that this endpoint gets invoked on the first request, not at container startup, so I need to handle the model pulling carefully to avoid blocking the initial request too long.\n\nActually, looking at Modal's architecture more carefully—`@modal.enter()` runs once when the container boots, not per-request. So I can safely pull the model during initialization without impacting request latency. I'll add the pull command to `start_server` and increase the timeout to give the model download enough time to complete.","thinkingSignature":"6fd538ac23c7e01a516d98873f3be2ef63d60a05a63458f6d5927428117e1d5e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8ka56reuvmfr_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\deploy\\modal_ollama.py","oldText":"    @modal.enter()\n    def start_server(self):\n        import subprocess, os, signal, sys\n\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] Starting ollama serve...\", file=sys.stderr)\n        self._process = subprocess.Popen(\n            [\"ollama\", \"serve\"],\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n            preexec_fn=os.setsid,\n        )\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] ollama serve started, pid=\", self._process.pid, file=sys.stderr)","newText":"    @modal.enter()\n    def start_server(self):\n        import subprocess, os, signal, sys, time\n\n        # Pull model first (runs once per container cold start)\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] Pulling qwen2.5:7b model...\", file=sys.stderr)\n        pull = subprocess.run(\n            [\"ollama\", \"pull\", \"qwen2.5:7b\"],\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n            timeout=600,  # allow up to 10min for model pull\n        )\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] Model ready, starting ollama serve...\", file=sys.stderr)\n        self._process = subprocess.Popen(\n            [\"ollama\", \"serve\"],\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n            preexec_fn=os.setsid,\n        )\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] ollama serve started, pid=\", self._process.pid, file=sys.stderr)"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":31111,"output":655,"cacheRead":13714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45480,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774276079995}}
