{"type":"message","id":"b80e809d","parentId":"b0d49a7c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:33:52.648Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still getting Method Not Allowed. The issue is with the FastAPI routing. Let me look at this more carefully.\n\nThe `generate` method has `@modal.fastapi_endpoint(label=\"spark-ollama-qwen-generate\")`. In Modal's FastAPI integration, the endpoint path is determined by the function name. So it should be at `/generate`.\n\nBut wait - maybe Modal's `fastapi_endpoint` doesn't use `label` that way. Let me check what the actual URL structure is. The app was previously deployed with two endpoints:\n- `spark-ollama-qwen-health` → health endpoint\n- `spark-ollama-qwen-generate` → generate endpoint\n\n\nThese are separate endpoints with different labels, so they should map to different paths. But `POST /generate` returned 404 while `POST /` returns 405, which suggests the FastAPI app is mounted at the root but the `/generate` route isn't registered. I think the issue is that Modal's `fastapi_endpoint` decorator creates independent web endpoints, so I need to figure out what URL path each function actually gets mounted at.\n\nLooking at the Modal documentation more carefully, `@modal.fastapi_endpoint()` exposes the function as an endpoint at `/{function_name}` by default, which means `generate` should be at `/generate`. But the logs show `POST /generate` returns 404, so either the new deployment hasn't started its container yet, or the function isn't being registered at that path.\n\nSince the new deployment with the model pull logic just happened, the container is likely still initializing and pulling the model. I should try a few more times or check the logs to see what's actually happening with the endpoint registration.","thinkingSignature":"83192dc4a8d63f20b9b10fadfa544d833f946355358b2767856e6d82884df176"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fskt4ljc6qmh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"modal app