{"type":"message","id":"2ab6180f","parentId":"79e21f9e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:35:33.486Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, redeployed. Now I need to wait for the new container to start and pull the model. This will take a few minutes. Let me poll the health endpoint to see when the container is up.\n\nAlso, I need to figure out the correct URL for the generate endpoint. The issue with routing could be that:\n1. The `fastapi_endpoint` decorator exposes the function at `/` (root), not `/generate`\n2. But `POST /` returns 405\n\nIf the generate endpoint is at `/`, then I should be able to POST JSON to it. But it returned 405. This is confusing.\n\nWait - looking at the Modal docs more carefully: `@modal.fastapi_endpoint()` - when used inside a `@modal.cls()` class, it creates an endpoint at the path `/{method_name}`. So it should be at `/generate`.\n \nBut the logs show `POST /generate` returning 404, which shouldn't happen if the endpoint exists. Maybe there's a Modal-side routing issue, or the web endpoint URL structure is different than I'm thinking. The `label` parameter in `@modal.fastapi_endpoint(label=\"...\")` probably affects the URL slug rather than the HTTP method path itself.\n\nLooking at the actual Modal documentation examples, the endpoints at `https://greeter-srv.modal.run` and `https://辨哀--web-1-mlazaar-70.evaluela-03.modal.run` suggest the path should just be `/`, not `/generate`. So the `label` creates the subdomain, and the actual route path is probably `/`. This means I need to POST directly to `https://toxzak-svg--spark-ollama-qwen-generate.modal.run/` rather than adding `/generate` to the path.\n\nBut that still leaves the 405 Method Not Allowed error - FastAPI defaults to GET for root paths, so I'd need to explicitly set `method=\"POST\"` in the decorator. Actually, thinking about this more carefully: if `generate` is decorated with `fastapi_endpoint` inside a `@app.cls()` class, Modal might be mounting the entire class's FastAPI app at the root path, which would explain why the method name isn't part of the URL path at all.\n\nThe 405 on POST to `/` while GET works suggests the endpoint function only accepts GET requests by default. I should just switch to `modal.web_endpoint` instead, which is simpler and more straightforward for this use case.","thinkingSignature":"03f485644136c804436b62bc5ca5169c77c80b10baf0698f682c9767696b588d"},{"type":"text","text":"While that spins up (2-5 min cold start + model pull), let me fix the routing issue I saw — `POST /` returning 405 means the FastAPI function isn't configured for POST. Switching to Modal's simpler `web_endpoint`:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_k1v7v0xso6c2_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\deploy\\modal_ollama.py","oldText":"    @modal.fastapi_endpoint(label=\"spark-ollama-qwen-generate\")\n    def generate(self, body: dict):\n        \"\"\"\n        body: { prompt: str, model?: str = \"qwen2.5:7b\", options?: { temperature?, num_predict? } }\n        \"\"\"\n        import requests\n\n        payload = {\n            \"model\": body.get(\"model\", \"qwen2.5:7b\"),\n            \"prompt\": body.get(\"prompt\", \"\"),\n            \"stream\": False,\n            \"options\": body.get(\"options\", {}),\n        }\n        resp = requests.post(\n            \"http://localhost:11434/api/generate\",\n            json=payload,\n            timeout=120,\n        )\n        resp.raise_for_status()\n        return {\"response\": resp.json().get(\"response\", \"\"), \"model\": payload[\"model\"]}\n\n    @modal.fastapi_endpoint(label=\"spark-ollama-qwen-health\")\n    def health(self):\n        return {\"status\": \"ok\", \"service\": \"spark-ollama\", \"model\": \"qwen2.5:7b\"}","newText":"    @modal.web_endpoint(label=\"spark-ollama-qwen-generate\", method=\"POST\")\n    def generate(self, body: dict):\n        \"\"\"\n        body: { prompt: str, model?: s