{"type":"message","id":"461866e4","parentId":"0a225030","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:39:34.318Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the new container IS running (with the model pull logic), but the Ollama API at `localhost:11434/api/generate` is still returning 404. This means:1. Ollama serve IS running (it started successfully)\n2. But the model `qwen2.5:7b` is NOT available (404 from `/api/generate`)\n\nThe issue is that the `ollama pull` command runs during the `@modal.enter()` phase, but:\n1. It may not have finished yet when the first request comes in\n2. OR the model pull didn't succeed properly\n\nWait, looking at the logs:\n\n\nThe container started and pulled the model successfully, but then when the POST request came in, it hit Ollama's API and got a 404 for the model. So the model pull completed in the startup phase, but when I tried to actually use it with a generate request, Ollama didn't recognize the model. The `ollama pull` command should have made the model available, but something's not connecting properly between the pull and the serve processes. The container is definitely new since it shows \"Model ready, starting ollama serve...\" but the model still isn't being recognized by the API. I'm thinking the `ollama pull` might be downloading the model to a different directory than what Ollama serve is actually looking at when it starts. Let me try explicitly setting `OLLAMA_MODELS` to `/root/.ollama` during the pull command, or maybe I should switch to using the Ollama API's built-in pull endpoint instead of the CLI.\n\nActually, I should just increase the timeout on the pull command—maybe 10 minutes isn't long enough for the model to download. Let me bump it up to 15 minutes and also verify that the Ollama serve process is actually starting with the right environment variable pointing to the correct models directory.","thinkingSignature":"afcf97d53388ba405539edf4bf6f225f6721982f40bff97c49930b705fc11753"},{"type":"text","text":"The model pull seems to not have finished before serve started, or the model isn't where Ollama expects. Let me fix the startup to wait for the pull AND serve to fully initialize:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7qna5rfnq4gx_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\deploy\\modal_ollama.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":37471,"output":468,"cacheRead":13714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51653,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774276758595}}
{"type":"message","id":"c48ddbb4","parentId":"461866e4","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:39:34.455Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7qna5rfnq4gx_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nSPARK Ollama GPU endpoint on Modal\nDeploy: modal deploy spark.deploy.modal_ollama\nEndpoint: https://spark-ollama-qwen-{user}.modal.run\n\"\"\"\n\nimport modal\n\napp = modal.App(\"spark-ollama\")\n\nollama_image = (\n    modal.Image.debian_slim(python_version=\"3.11\")\n    .pip_install(\"requests\", \"httpx\", \"fastapi[standard]\")\n    .run_commands(\n        \"apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl zstd && curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\",\n    )\n    .env({\"OLLAMA_MODELS\": \"/root/.ollama\"})\n)\n\n\n@app.cls(\n    image=ollama_image,\n    gpu=\"T4\",  # cheapest GPU on Modal (~0.30/hr)\n    memory=16384,\n    scaledown_window=600,\n    timeout=3600,\n)\nclass OllamaEndpoint:\n    \"\"\"\n    Ollama on T4 GPU. Model pulled at container start (~2-5min cold start).\n    After that, subsequent requests are fast.\n\n    Endpoints:\n      POST https://toxzak-svg--spark-ollama-qwen-generate.modal.run/\n        body: { prompt, model?, options? }\n      GET https://toxzak-svg--spark-ollama-qwen-health.modal.run/\n    \"\"\"\n\n    @modal.enter()\n    def start_server(self):\n        import subprocess, os, signal, sys, time\n\n        # Pull model first (runs once per container cold start)\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] Pulling qwen2.5:7b model...\", file=sys.stderr)\n        pull = subprocess.run(\n            [\"ollama\", \"pull\", \"qwen2.5:7b\"],\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n            timeout=600,  # allow up to 10min for model pull\n        )\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] Model ready, starting ollama serve...\", file=sys.stderr)\n        self._process = subprocess.Popen(\n            [\"ollama\", \"serve\"],\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n            preexec_fn=os.setsid,\n        )\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] ollama serve started, pid=\", self._process.pid, file=sys.stderr)\n\n    @modal.exit()\n    def stop_server(self):\n        import os, signal, sys\n\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] Shutting down...\", file=sys.stderr)\n        try:\n            os.killpg(os.getpgid(self._process.pid), signal.SIGTERM)\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n\n    @modal.web_endpoint(label=\"spark-ollama-qwen-generate\", method=\"POST\")\n    def generate(self, body: dict):\n        \"\"\"\n        body: { prompt: str, model?: str = \"qwen2.5:7b\", options?: { temperature?, num_predict? } }\n        \"\"\"\n        import requests\n\n        payload = {\n            \"model\": body.get(\"model\", \"qwen2.5:7b\"),\n            \"prompt\": body.get(\"prompt\", \"\"),\n            \"stream\": False,\n            \"options\": body.get(\"options\", {}),\n        }\n        resp = requests.post(\n            \"http://localhost:11434/api/generate\",\n            json=payload,\n            timeout=120,\n        )\n        resp.raise_for_status()\n        return {\"response\": resp.json().get(\"response\", \"\"), \"model\": payload[\"model\"]}\n\n    @modal.web_endpoint(label=\"spark-ollama-qwen-health\", method=\"GET\")\n    def health(self):\n        return {\"status\": \"ok\", \"service\": \"spark-ollama\", \"model\": \"qwen2.5:7b\"}\n\n\n@app.local_entrypoint()\ndef test():\n    print(\"spark-ollama module loaded OK\")\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774276774420}}
{"type":"message","id":"276a1e84","parentId":"c48ddbb4","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:39:59.976Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The problem is clear now: the `ollama pull` is run in the `@modal.enter()` method, which has a default timeout of 5 minutes in Modal (the `timeout=3600` on the class is for the entire container lifecycle, not the enter method). If the pull doesn't complete in the enter timeout, it gets killed.\n\nAlso, even after pull completes, the model might not be available if `ollama serve` isn't fully initialized when the first request hits.\n\nLet me try a completely different approach:\n1. In `@modal.enter()`, start `ollama serve` in the background\n2. Then call `ollama pull` (which downloads if needed)\n\n\n3. Wait for Ollama to be ready by polling the API\n4. The `ollama pull` command should handle checking if the model already exists and skip re-downloading it\n\nActually, I'm realizing the real issue might be that `ollama serve` needs to be running before I can call `ollama pull` at all, since pull communicates with the server via the API. So the sequence should be: start the server in the background, wait for it to be ready, then run the pull command.\n\nLooking at the logs more carefully though - the model pull succeeded (\"Model ready, starting ollama serve...\") but then requests still return 404. This could mean the serve process isn't fully initialized by the time the first request arrives, or there's something else going wrong. Let me try bumping up the enter timeout since the default Modal limit is probably much shorter than the 10 minutes we need for the full pull and serve startup sequence.\n\nActually, I think the cleaner approach is to have `ollama serve` start first, then run `ollama pull` as an API call rather than a CLI command - that way the pull operation goes through the server itself and we can better manage the timing. I could also add a brief sleep after starting the server to let it initialize before attempting any operations.\n\nLet me refactor this with explicit health checking between each step - start the server, wait for it to be ready, then pull the model. Though I need to verify that `ollama serve` stays running in the background when started with `nohup` or `subprocess.Popen` with specific arguments.\n\nActually, I think the real issue might be that `ollama serve` needs the `OLLAMA_MODELS` environment variable set to know where to store models, and it has its own environment handling that I need to account for.","thinkingSignature":"19f64dbaff1fee898ac0fa902eec30563efbb11d00418623858a62defc5039da"},{"type":"text","text":"The issue is that `ollama serve` starts but isn't fully ready when requests come in. Let me rewrite the startup to wait for Ollama to be ready before serving:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_anpkg2grqosu_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\deploy\\modal_ollama.py","oldText":"    @modal.enter()\n    def start_server(self):\n        import subprocess, os, signal, sys, time\n\n        # Pull model first (runs once per container cold start)\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] Pulling qwen2.5:7b model...\", file=sys.stderr)\n        pull = subprocess.run(\n            [\"ollama\", \"pull\", \"qwen2.5:7b\"],\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n            timeout=600,  # allow up to 10min for model pull\n        )\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] Model ready, starting ollama serve...\", file=sys.stderr)\n        self._process = subprocess.Popen(\n            [\"ollama\", \"serve\"],\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n            preexec_fn=os.setsid,\n        )\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] ollama serve started, pid=\", self._process.pid, file=sys.stderr)","newText":"    @modal.enter()\n    def start_server(self):\n        import subprocess, os, signal, sys, time, requests, urllib3\n        urllib3.disable_warnings(urllib3.exceptions.InsecureRequestWarning)\n\n        # 1. Start ollama serve in background\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] Starting ollama serve...\", file=sys.stderr)\n        self._process = subprocess.Popen(\n            [\"ollama\", \"serve\"],\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n            preexec_fn=os.setsid,\n        )\n\n        # 2. Wait for ollama to be ready (poll /api/tags)\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] Waiting for ollama to be ready...\", file=sys.stderr)\n        for i in range(60):  # up to 60s\n            try:\n                r = requests.get(\"http://localhost:11434/api/tags\", timeout=5)\n                if r.ok:\n                    break\n            except Exception:\n                pass\n            time.sleep(1)\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] Ollama is ready.\", file=sys.stderr)\n\n        # 3. Pull model (if not already cached)\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] Pulling qwen2.5:7b model...\", file=sys.stderr)\n        pull = subprocess.run(\n            [\"ollama\", \"pull\", \"qwen2.5:7b\"],\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n            timeout=900,  # up to 15min for model download\n        )\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] Model ready. Server running pid=\", self._process.pid, file=sys.stderr)"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":38773,"output":1191,"cacheRead":13714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53678,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774276774459}}
