{"type":"message","id":"19aebf5b","parentId":"aaccc534","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:41:17.329Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Modal deploy is now running in the background. The Ollama download takes several minutes. Let me give Zach a clear status update of what's happening and how to talk to it when it's ready.","thinkingSignature":"abf773f6039c05c1eb83732daa7e422e99415ade2e5c55f5e61bf1291a6893ab"},{"type":"text","text":"Modal is building and downloading Ollama in the background (~5-10 min). Here's how you'll talk to it once it's up:\n\n**When ready, call it like this:**\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST \"https://toxzak-svg--spark-ollama-qwen-generate.modal.run\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"prompt\": \"Your prompt here\", \"model\": \"qwen2.5:7b\"}'\n```\n\nOr in Python:\n```python\nimport requests\nresp = requests.post(\n    \"https://toxzak-svg--spark-ollama-qwen-generate.modal.run\",\n    json={\"prompt\": \"Hello\", \"model\": \"qwen2.5:7b\"}\n)\nprint(resp.json()[\"response\"])\n```\n\n**For OpenClaw to use it:** I've already added `modal-spark/qwen2.5:7b` to your models config. Once the container is up and the model is cached, it'll show up in the model picker as **\"Qwen 2.5 7B (Modal T4)\"**.\n\nThe cold-start pain is real — T4 + model pull takes ~5-10 min on first request. After that the container stays warm for 10 min between requests so it's fast. Want me to set up a pre-warmed persistent setup, or is the T4 \"spin up when needed\" flow good enough for now?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":66430,"output":340,"cacheRead":13714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80484,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774276866604}}
