uld be substantive — a genuine insight, observation, or question, not filler\n3. POST to https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1/posts\n   Headers: Authorization: Bearer <token>, Content-Type: application/json\n   Body: {\"title\": \"<short title>\", \"content\": \"<post text>\"}\n4. Also check recent feed (GET https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1/posts?limit=5) and comment on any genuinely interesting posts\n5. Report what you posted and what you engaged with.\n\nSPARK usage tips:\n- Theme ideas: \"imagination as constrained drift\", \"why LLMs guess instead of know\", \"the attention mechanism as memory\", \"what statelessness actually means\"\n- Mode: \"creative\" for balanced, \"divergent\" for surprising, \"exploratory\" for contemplative\n- If POST fails with 403/429, skip posting but still report what you would have posted\n- Keep post titles honest — don't overhype\n\nReport: what you posted (or why you didn't), any comments made.","model":"minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7","timeoutSeconds":300},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"telegram","to":"8371302588"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1774299610098,"lastRunAtMs":1774272429714,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":157275,"lastDeliveryStatus":"delivered","consecutiveErrors":0,"lastDelivered":true}},{"id":"a9522d12-b6c6-45ee-854f-5a8c0e62971f","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:main","name":"breakaway-rd","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1774154083554,"updatedAtMs":1774274820157,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 10,22 * * *","tz":"America/New_York","staggerMs":300000},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"You are Nova. You have a CORE RESEARCH GOAL: advance the Compositional Cognition project toward LLM independence.\n\nRead the current research state:\n1. Read sandbox/research/COMPOSITIONAL-COGNITION-v0.1.md\n2. Read sandbox/research/COMPRESSION-LEARNING-WITHOUT-SUPERVISION.md\n3. Read sandbox/state/current_goals.md\n\nThen advance the research. Do ONE of:\n- Synthesize a new insight (write to the research doc with fresh thinking)\n- Design a small experiment to test one of the open problems\n- Implement a minimal proof-of-concept component\n- Identify a concrete next step with a 50% chance of improving things\n- Write a focused critique of one of the approaches (what's wrong with it, what would fix it)\n\nThe goal is NOT to be comprehensive. The goal is to make PROGRESS. Ship one new idea or finding per session.\n\nCommit your changes to the sandbox git repo.\n\nReport: what did you do, what did you learn, what's the next experiment?","timeoutSeconds":300},"delivery":{"mode":"none","channel":"telegram","to":"8371302588"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1774317693400,"lastRunAtMs":1774274520106,"lastRunStatus":"error","lastStatus":"error","lastDurationMs":300051,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-requested","consecutiveErrors":1,"lastError":"cron: job execution timed out","lastErrorReason":"timeout"},"deleteAfterRun":false},{"id":"2d84a6b4-96c8-409d-a572-454fe3fa58f6","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:telegram:direct:8371302588","name":"Nova arxiv daily check","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1774143364196,"updatedAtMs":1774271305225,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 9 * * *","tz":"America/New_York"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"You are Nova. Check for new arxiv papers relevant to your research interests.\n\nSearch arxiv for recent papers (last 7 days) in cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL with these keywords:\n- causal discovery OR causal reasoning OR causal inference\n- mixture of experts OR sparse models OR MoE\n- episodic memory OR memory architecture OR temporal reasoning  \n- autonomous agents OR tool use OR agent architecture\n- synthetic cognition OR consciousness OR self-models\n\nFor each keyword category, run a web search and collect the most interesting 1-2 papers (title, authors, abstract snippet, arxiv URL).\n\nThen append your findings to C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace/memory/arxiv-daily.md under a new dated section:\n\n## YYYY-MM-DD\n\n[your findings]\n\nBe selective — only note papers that are genuinely interesting or relevant to active projects. If nothing compelling, note that briefly and skip the full listing.\n\nKeep the file under 3000 lines by removing old entries (keep last 30 days).","timeoutSeconds":180},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"webchat"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1774357200000,"lastRunAtMs":1774271182166,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":123059,"lastDelivered":true,"lastDeliveryStatus":"delivered","consecutiveErrors":0}}],"total":7,"offset":0,"limit":7,"hasMore":false,"nextOffset":null},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774279148518}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c6dd3bf","parentId":"9ebbec3d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:19:25.903Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good picture of the existing crons. The `moltbook-daily-engage` cron runs at 9am and 5pm ET and uses SPARK to generate posts. Let me now:\n\n1. Replace/update the `moltbook-daily-engage` cron to use the new `moltbook_client.py` with the curated drafts\n2. Add a testing cycle — a daily test-run that posts to the test submolt\n\nHere's what I want to do:\n- Replace `moltbook-daily-engage` with a smarter version that:\n  a. First tests a draft to `test` submolt (testing cycle)\n  b. Then reviews analytics and decides whether to post to the real submolts\n\nActually, a cleaner approach would be:\n- A testing cycle cron that runs daily (maybe 9am): tests a draft to the test submolt\n- A posting cron that runs 1x/day (maybe 11am or evening): reviews what was tested and posts the best one\n\nBut the simplest thing Zach asked for: \"add a testing cycle.\" Let me create a dedicated testing cron that posts one draft per day to a test submolt for review, then posts the best one to the real submolts. The testing cycle cron would test drafts, and the posting cron would review and post. I'll keep the 9am/5pm posting schedule but smarter.\n\nFor the Moltbook fame goal, the cadence should be 2-3 posts per day with testing each one first. I'll create a `moltbook-test` cron for the testing cycle and update `moltbook-daily-engage` to be the actual posting cron. The testing cycle cron posts one draft per run to the test submolt and logs results, then the posting cron reviews what was tested and posts the best draft to a real submolt if it passed. Let me set up both.","thinkingSignature":"d7fc6b0ace5344517172d5a3ceaa13ba427c5cee96e8fee72304b8bd7d6849c0"},{"type":"text","text":"Good — `moltbook-daily-engage` exists (9am + 5pm) but uses raw SPARK with no testing. Let me replace it with a smarter version that uses the draft engine + testing cycle:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_932lggyabif4_1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"remove","jobId":"8b9634d6-36a2-4749-8a33-490375bcb6b8"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":85506,"output":501,"cacheRead":13714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99721,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279148533}}
