{"type":"message","id":"6c40133c","parentId":"860c5e0e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:20:45.123Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_mwohcgarvv13_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# PENDING ACTIONS\nLast updated: 2026-03-21\n\n## Promises Made\n(None yet)\n\n## Deferred Tasks\n(None yet)\n\n## Flagged for Review\n(None yet)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774279245111}}
{"type":"message","id":"fd11323b","parentId":"6c40133c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:20:45.133Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_mwohcgarvv13_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-22 0125\n\n## Active\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\n\n## Completed This Session\n\n### Architecture Cross-Analysis ✅\n- Compared Compositional Cognition vs TemporalAttention vs Infant\n- Key finding: all three architectures are compatible and complementary\n- Full analysis: `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\n\n### Gap-Decay Synthesis ✅ (derived across 17+ pulses)\n- Session gaps = decay mechanism, not amnesia\n- λ parameter encodes BOTH decay rate AND gap sensitivity threshold\n- TemporalAttention focus_decay + Breakaway gaps = same phenomenon\n- Full synthesis: `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`\n\n### LLM-Augmented Pulse ✅\n- pulse.ps1 now calls MiniMax-M2.7 API on each pulse\n- Thinking is coherent and building across pulses\n- Key files: `.llm_key`, `pulse.ps1`\n\n## Pending\n- [ ] Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\n- [ ] Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\n- [ ] Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\n- [ ] Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\n\n## Phase 1 Advancement: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY (2026-03-23)\n- **Insight:** Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\n- **New doc:** `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\n- **Hypothesis:** Causal structure IS invariant structure — compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation\n- **Next experiment:** Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) — test on last 20 pulse logs\n- **Success criteria:** >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\n- **Implication:** Phase 1 and Phase 2 collapse into one unified problem\n\n## Key Insights from This Session\n\n1. **The gap IS the compression** — session boundaries are temporal hashing\n2. **λ encodes both** — decay rate and gap threshold are the same parameter\n3. **Three architectures, one synthesis** — Infant (catastrophic forgetting), TemporalAttention (focus decay), Breakaway (discontinuity) are complementary, not competing\n4. **Breakaway's unique bet holds** — session gaps as compression is novel and correct\n\n## Notes\n- Breakaway is stateless — each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\n- Pulse script: active hours check DISABLED (authorized by Zach, 24/7 operation)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774279245123}}
