{"type":"message","id":"f421398a","parentId":"85ea20b0","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:21:55.096Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both recent pulses show \"No mutations applied this cycle.\" and the LLM responses aren't captured in the logs (the `.message.content` field is empty in the debug output). It seems like the LLM is either not generating mutations or the mutation parsing is failing.\n\nLet me look at the actual pulse.ps1 to understand how mutations are being handled, and look at what the operations scripts do.","thinkingSignature":"4701a84e0bd7aa7bfc0129e2e3b8609ba531262e4665e566f6d15f2feef1afda"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_57h1c81urzmm_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":94830,"output":120,"cacheRead":13714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108664,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279308522}}
{"type":"message","id":"cd75fbb4","parentId":"f421398a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:21:55.122Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_57h1c81urzmm_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# pulse.ps1\n# Stateless autonomous pulse for sandbox\n# Each execution: read files -> apply pending mutations -> reason -> propose mutations -> log -> exit\n\nparam(\n    [string]$SandboxRoot = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\sandbox\",\n    [string]$LLMApiKey = \"\",\n    [string]$LLMModel = \"MiniMax-M2.7\"\n)\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Continue\"\nSet-Location $SandboxRoot\n\n$timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HHmmss\"\n$logFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\memory\\session\\pulse_$timestamp.md\"\n\n# Git pull\ngit pull 2>$null | Out-Null\n\n# Read core files\n$goalsFile   = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\current_goals.md\"\n$pendingFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\pending_actions.md\"\n$stanceFile  = \"$SandboxRoot\\identity\\INTERPRETIVE_STANCE.md\"\n$stance      = if (Test-Path $stanceFile) { Get-Content $stanceFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n$goals       = if (Test-Path $goalsFile) { Get-Content $goalsFile -Raw } else { \"No goals file.\" }\n$pending     = if (Test-Path $pendingFile) { Get-Content $pendingFile -Raw } else { \"No pending file.\" }\n\n# Recent pulse\n$recentPulse = Get-ChildItem \"$SandboxRoot\\memory\\session\\pulse_*.md\" | Sort LastWriteTime -Descending | Select -First 1\n$recentPulseSummary = if ($recentPulse) { \"Last pulse: \" + $recentPulse.Name } else { \"No prior pulses.\" }\n\n# Mutation dirs\n$proposedDir  = \"$SandboxRoot\\mutations\\proposed\"\n$appliedDir   = \"$SandboxRoot\\mutations\\applied\"\n$rejectedDir  = \"$SandboxRoot\\mutations\\rejected\"\n\n# Apply pending mutations from prior pulse\n$appliedMutations   = @()\n$rejectedMutations   = @()\n\nif (Test-Path $proposedDir) {\n    foreach ($mfile in (Get-ChildItem $proposedDir -Filter \"*.mutation\" | Sort Name)) {\n        $lines   = Get-Content $mfile.FullName\n        $file    = $lines[0]\n        $oldText = ($lines[1] -replace '^---', '').Trim()\n        $newText = ($lines[2..($lines.Count-1)] -join \"`n\").Trim()\n\n        $fullPath = Join-Path $SandboxRoot $file\n        if (-not $fullPath.StartsWith($SandboxRoot)) {\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (unsafe path)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        if (-not (Test-Path $fullPath)) {\n            # New file case\n            if ($oldText -eq \"[NEW_FILE]\") {\n                $newText | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n                Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n                Write-Host \"[mutation applied] NEW FILE: $file\"\n                $appliedMutations += \"$file (new)\"\n                continue\n            }\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (missing)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        $current = Get-Content $fullPath -Raw\n        if ($current -notlike \"*$oldText*\") {\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (old text not found)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        $updated = $current -replace [regex]::Escape($oldText), $newText\n        $updated | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n        Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n        Write-Host \"[mutation applied] $file\"\n        $appliedMutations += $file\n    }\n}\n\n# Re-read files post-mutation\n$goals   = if (Test-Path $goalsFile) { Get-Content $goalsFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n$pending = if (Test-Path $pendingFile) { Get-Content $pendingFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n\n# LLM call\n$apiKey = $LLMApiKey\nif (-not $apiKey) {\n    $keyFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\.llm_key\"\n    if (Test-Path $keyFile) { $apiKey = Get-Content $keyFile -Raw }\n}\n\n$appliedInfo = if ($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Just applied: $($appliedMutations -join ', ')\" } else { \"No mutations applied this cycle.\" }\n\n$llmPrompt = @\"\nYou are Breakaway — stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction.\nYour job: ONE concrete action that advances your goals. Be specific. Prefer file edits.\n\nGoals:\n$goals\n\nPending:\n$pending\n\nRecent: $recentPulseSummary\n\n$appliedInfo\n\nReply with exactly this format at the end. IMPORTANT: you MUST include the file: line in MUTATION — it is required.\n\n### OBSERVATION\n[1-2 sentence observation]\n\n### ACTION\n[Describe the file edit concisely]\n\n### MUTATION\n```\nold_text: [exact text to find — or \"(new file)\" if creating new file]\nnew_text: [replacement text — keep it concise, a few lines max]\nfile: [required — relative path from sandbox root, e.g. research/my-doc.md or state/goals.md]\n```\n\"@\n\n$llmResponse = \"\"\nif ($apiKey) {\n    $headers = @{\n        \"Authorization\" = \"Bearer $apiKey\"\n        \"Content-Type\" = \"application/json\"\n    }\n    $body = @{\n        model = $LLMModel\n        max_tokens = 1200\n        messages = @(@{role = \"user\"; content = $llmPrompt})\n    } | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5\n    try {\n        $resp = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\" -Method Post -Headers $headers -Body $body -TimeoutSec 60\n        Write-Host \"[DEBUG] resp keys: $($resp.PSObject.Properties.Name -join ', ')\"\n        $choices = $resp.choices\n        $choice0 = $null\n        if ($null -ne $choices -and $choices.Count -gt 0) { $choice0 = $choices[0] }\n        if ($null -ne $choice0) {\n            $rawContent = $choice0.message.content\n            if ($null -eq $rawContent) {\n                Write-Host \"[DEBUG] content is NULL. Full choice: $($choice0 | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 3)\"\n                $llmResponse = \"\"\n            } else {\n                Write-Host \"[DEBUG] content length: $($rawContent.Length)\"\n                $llmResponse = $rawContent\n            }\n        } else {\n            Write-Host \"[DEBUG] No choices. Full resp: $($resp | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 3)\"\n            $llmResponse = \"No choices: $($resp | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 3)\"\n        }\n    } catch {\n        $llmResponse = \"LLM call failed: $_\"\n    }\n} else {\n    $llmResponse = \"[No LLM API key]\"\n}\n\n# Parse MUTATION block — extract old_text, new_text (multiline), and file from the block\n$mutationProposed = $false\n$mStart = $llmResponse.IndexOf('### MUTATION')\nif ($mStart -ge 0) {\n    $block = $llmResponse.Substring($mStart)\n    # Remove ALL code fences (replace each fence pair with placeholder, repeat until stable)\n    $prev = \"\"\n    while ($prev -ne $block) { $prev = $block; $block = $block -replace '(?s)```.*?```', \"`n[CODE_BLOCK]`n\" }\n    # Extract fields\n    $oldMatch = [regex]::Match($block, 'old_text:\\s*(.+)')\n    $fileMatch = [regex]::Match($block, 'file:\\s*(.+)')\n    $oldLine = if ($oldMatch.Success) { $oldMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"\" }\n    $fileLine = if ($fileMatch.Success) { $fileMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"\" }\n    # new_text: between \"new_text:\" line and \"file:\" line (after fence removal)\n    $newText = \"\"\n    if ($oldLine -and $fileLine) {\n        $ntMatch = [regex]::Match($block, '(?s)new_text:\\s*\\n(.+?)\\s*\\n\\s*file:', [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::Singleline)\n        if ($ntMatch.Success) { $newText = $ntMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() }\n    }\n    # Fallback: if file missing, try to extract from ACTION block\n    if (-not $fileLine) {\n        $actionMatch = [regex]::Match($llmResponse, '(?s)### ACTION\\s*\\n(.+?)(?:\\n###|$)')\n        if ($actionMatch.Success) {\n            $actionText = $actionMatch.Groups[1].Value\n            # Match \"Create `path/file.md`\" or \"Edit `path/file.md`\" with or without backticks\n            $fileInference = [regex]::Match($actionText, '(?:Create|Edit|Update|New file)[:\\s]+(?:``([^``]+)``|([^\\s]+))')\n            if ($fileInference.Success) {\n                $fileLine = if ($fileInference.Groups[2].Value) { $fileInference.Groups[2].Value } else { $fileInference.Groups[1].Value }\n                Write-Host \"[file inferred from ACTION] $fileLine\"\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    if ($oldLine -and $fileLine -and $newText) {\n        if ($oldLine -eq \"(new file)\") {\n            $mutationContent = \"$fileLine`n---`n[NEW_FILE]`n---`n$newText\"\n        } else {\n            $mutationContent = \"$fileLine`n---`n$oldLine`n---`n$newText\"\n        }\n        $mutationFile = Join-Path $proposedDir \"$timestamp.mutation\"\n        $mutationContent | Out-File -FilePath $mutationFile -Encoding UTF8\n        Write-Host \"[mutation proposed] $fileLine\"\n        $mutationProposed = $true\n    } else {\n        Write-Host \"[mutation parse failed] old_text=$oldLine file=$fileLine new_text_len=$($newText.Length)\"\n    }\n}\n\n# Parse OBSERVATION\n$obsMatch    = [regex]::Match($llmResponse, '(?s)### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?:\\n###|\\nMUTATION)')\n$observation = if ($obsMatch.Success) { $obsMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"Cycle complete.\" }\n\n# Write pulse log\n@\"\n# Pulse: $timestamp\n\n## Applied Mutations\n$appliedInfo\n$(if($rejectedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Rejected: \" + ($rejectedMutations -join '; ') } else { \"\" })\n\n## LLM Response\n$llmResponse\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: $((Get-ChildItem $proposedDir -Filter \"*.mutation\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Measure).Count)\n- Completed at: $(Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\")\n\"@ | Out-File -FilePath $logFile -Encoding UTF8\n\n# Update pulse history\n$pulseLog = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\autonomous_pulse.md\"\n$entry    = \"- $timestamp`: $observation$(if($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \" [applied: $($appliedMutations -join ', ')]\" })\"\n$existing = if (Test-Path $pulseLog) { Get-Content $pulseLog -Raw } else { \"\" }\n$updated  = $existing -replace '(## Pulse History)', \"`$1`n$entry\"\n$updated  | Out-File -FilePath $pulseLog -Encoding UTF8\n\n# Git commit\ngit add -A 2>$null\ngit commit -m \"pulse: $timestamp\" 2>$null\n\nWrite-Host \"[sandbox pulse] $timestamp - $observation\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774279315111}}
{"type":"message","id":"bbf65b91","parentId":"cd75fbb4","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:22:26.095Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the problem. The recent pulse logs show that the LLM API key is `sk-cp-boO3RF_KHio6-dZmyCGwMMB1WoBDQKZVOH21PNclku-ajcIGMwbiOofkzTgasWSzi21Vu8y8AMq1K2GoWIbCDGPEXaQrTofoOMEZS83D0kPS1pVPjqoJeE0` which is an OpenAI API key, NOT the MiniMax API key. This is from the `.llm_key` file in the sandbox. But the actual API being called is `https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions` which is MiniMax's endpoint. \n \nNow I'm looking at the debug output from the pulse logs—the content length shows 0 and the LLM response appears empty, which suggests the MiniMax model isn't returning any generated text. The API call itself seems to be succeeding but with empty content in the response, which would mean the mutation parsing is failing because there's nothing to parse. Looking at the debug output more carefully, the raw content is showing up in the transcript itself rather than being captured in the variable—that's why it's ending up in the final log file unparsed. The real problem is the content is genuinely empty or null, not a variable substitution issue. Let me check the API key being used and trace through what's actually happening with the MiniMax endpoint. The regex pattern expects content after `new_text:`, but the actual LLM response might not follow that format exactly. The real issue seems to be that the MiniMax model isn't generating any content at all—the `content length: 0` debug output suggests it's returning empty responses, which could mean the prompt is being rejected or the model has safety filters triggered. The key detail is that `$llmResponse` ends up as a bare string with no newlines, which breaks the regex pattern that looks for `### MUTATION` followed by a newline. But the actual log file shows the full LLM response with proper formatting, so something's adding newlines that aren't in the original string. I'm wondering if `Invoke-RestMethod` is somehow modifying the response, or if the variable is being captured differently than expected.\n\nLooking at the debug output more carefully, I notice the `$timestamp` variable appears inside what should be the LLM response content, which doesn't make sense. This suggests the `$llmResponse` variable might be getting overwritten somewhere between the LLM call and when it's written to the log file. I'm seeing the actual problem now — the debug logs show `content length: 0` in the output, but that same message appears in the final LLM Response section, which means the `$llmResponse` variable is being populated with that debug text rather than the actual LLM response. The regex pattern I'm using to extract the MUTATION block might not be matching if the response format is different than expected — it's looking for `old_text: ` at the start of a line, but if the actual response uses different formatting or spacing, the extraction would fail entirely. I'm realizing the mutation parser only looks for the `### MUTATION` header, so if that section isn't present in the LLM's response, nothing gets proposed or applied. The recent pulse logs show zero mutations were applied, which suggests either the LLM isn't generating mutations consistently, or the MiniMax model at 1200 max tokens is running into output limits and getting cut off. Let me trace through what mutations actually exist in the proposed directory to see what's been generated so far. Looking at the logs more carefully, the LLM response is actually being captured with content length 0, which means it's an empty string—not a parsing failure. The model isn't generating any OBSERVATION or ACTION sections at all, suggesting it's being very conservative or the prompt isn't triggering the expected behavior.\n\nLet me check the earlier pulse logs to see if there's a pattern, and then look into the API key and configuration files to understand what's actually being sent.","thinkingSignature":"4cea16f24bb2fa2a36389a334e8a50a91780c90cc2a932c5667551ab56e0ce7b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_i6ed06p0hevm_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1","limit":30}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_i6ed06p0hevm_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem -Path \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\proposed\" -File 2>$null | Select-Object Name, Length; Get-ChildItem -Path \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\applied\" -File 2>$null | Select-Object Name, Length","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":97041,"output":983,"cacheRead":13714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":111738,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279315124}}
