{"type":"message","id":"9bf62b86","parentId":"979e48b6","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:22:44.578Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `.llm_key` is `sk-cp-boO3RF_KHio6-dZmyCGwMMB1WoBDQKZVOH21PNclku-ajcIGMwbiOofkzTgasWSzi21Vu8y8AMq1K2GoWIbCDGPEXaQrTofoOMEZS83D0kPS1pVPjqoJeE0` which is an OpenAI key. But the pulse.ps1 is calling `https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions`. That's a mismatch! The MiniMax API endpoint likely requires a MiniMax API key, not an OpenAI key.\n\n\nLet me test the MiniMax API directly with the credentials I have to see what's actually happening.","thinkingSignature":"b0a4bd8b11f9bd2f4dc37482bb30ff283c1bf701c01fd36361f35025e1343801"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j913djkhv0tp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$body = @{ model = \"MiniMax-M2.7\"; max_tokens = 200; messages = @(@{role = \"user\"; content = \"Say hello in exactly 5 words.\"}) } | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5; Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\" -Method POST -Headers @{ \"Authorization\" = \"Bearer sk-cp-boO3RF_KHio6-dZmyCGwMMB1WoBDQKZVOH21PNclku-ajcIGMwbiOofkzTgasWSzi21Vu8y8AMq1K2GoWIbCDGPEXaQrTofoOMEZS83D0kPS1pVPjqoJeE0\"; \"Content-Type\" = \"application/json\" } -Body $body -TimeoutSec 30 2>&1","yieldMs":25000,"timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":97006,"output":391,"cacheRead":13714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":111111,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279356577}}
