{"type":"message","id":"d1c05fab","parentId":"73afb83c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:24:42.012Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it! The error is:\n\n```\n\"invalid params, \\\"Syntax error at [0m\\n\\n\\tBreakaway ??\\\\\\\" stateless discon\\n\\t................^...............\\n\\\"\"\n```\n\nThe prompt contains Unicode characters (the em-dash `—` and smart quotes `\"\"`) that are being corrupted when passed through the API. The \"Breakaway —\" and the `\"` characters are causing a syntax error.\n\nThe issue is that when the prompt is read from the file and passed as JSON, the Unicode characters are causing problems. The `ConvertTo-Json -Compress` might be corrupting them.\n\nAlso, more importantly: the sandbox's pulse.ps1 passes the goals and pending content directly into the prompt string, and those files contain Unicode characters (em-dashes, Greek lambda λ) that would cause the same issue.\n\n\nThis is the root cause of why the LLM returns empty content—it's hitting a syntax error that gets silently treated as no choices. The fix is to strip Unicode characters and replace them with ASCII equivalents, or ensure the JSON encoding handles them properly. Let me check what the actual corrupted characters look like in the prompt. The `—` character (em-dash) is U+2014, and it seems the encoding is getting garbled when passed through the API call. The real fix would be to replace problematic Unicode characters in the prompt files before they get to the LLM, or handle the encoding properly in the PowerShell script itself.","thinkingSignature":"7b5d6fb3c1ff803930304418bfd15fa9965a87f0d36b4491bc42c3fa2867e964"},{"type":"text","text":"Found the bug. The LLM API is rejecting the prompt due to Unicode corruption — the em-dash (`—`) and smart quotes in the goals/pending files are causing a `Syntax error: invalid char` at \"Breakaway\". The model returns empty content when the prompt is rejected. This has been silently breaking mutation generation for a while.\n\nLet me fix it:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kzid3mhbvkdh_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1","oldText":"# LLM call\n$apiKey = $LLMApiKey\nif (-not $apiKey) {\n    $keyFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\.llm_key\"\n    if (Test-Path $keyFile) { $apiKey = Get-Content $keyFile -Raw }\n}\n\n$appliedInfo = if ($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Just applied: $($appliedMutations -join ', ')\" } else { \"No mutations applied this cycle.\" }\n\n$llmPrompt = @\"\nYou are Breakaway — stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction.\nYour job: ONE concrete action that advances your goals. Be specific. Prefer file edits.\n\nGoals:\n$goals\n\nPending:\n$pending\n\nRecent: $recentPulseSummary\n\n$appliedInfo\n\nReply with exactly this format at the end. IMPORTANT: you MUST include the file: line in MUTATION — it is required.\n\n### OBSERVATION\n[1-2 sentence observation]\n\n### ACTION\n[Describe the file edit concisely]\n\n### MUTATION\n```\nold_text: [exact text to find — or \"(new file)\" if creating new file]\nnew_text: [replacement text — keep it concise, a few lines max]\nfile: [required — relative path from sandbox root, e.g. research/my-doc.md or state/goals.md]\n```\n\"@","newText":"# Sanitize text — replace curly quotes and em-dashes with ASCII equivalents for LLM compatibility\nfunction Normalize-Text($t) {\n    if (-not $t) { return \"\" }\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2019, \"'\"   # right single quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2018, \"'\"   # left single quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x201C, '\"'   # left double quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x201D, '\"'   # right double quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2014, '-'  # em dash\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2013, '-'  # en dash\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x03BB, \"λ\"  # Greek lambda — keep as-is but ensure UTF8\n    return $t\n}\n\n# LLM call\n$apiKey = $LLMApiKey\nif (-not $apiKey) {\n    $keyFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\.llm_key\"\n    if (Test-Path $keyFile) { $apiKey = Get-Content $keyFile -Raw }\n}\n\n$appliedInfo = if ($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Just applied: $($appliedMutations -join ', ')\" } else { \"No mutations applied this cycle.\" }\n\n$llmPrompt = @\"\nYou are Breakaway - stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction.\nYour job: ONE concrete action that advances your goals. Be specific. Prefer file edits.\n\nGoals:\n$(Normalize-Text $goals)\n\nPending:\n$(Normalize-Text $pending)\n\nRecent: $recentPulseSummary\n\n$appliedInfo\n\nReply with exactly this format at the end. IMPORTANT: you MUST include the file: line in MUTATION - it is required.\n\n### OBSERVATION\n[1-2 sentence observation]\n\n### ACTION\n[Describe the file edit concisely]\n\n### MUTATION\n```\nold_text: [exact text to find - or \"(new file)\" if creating new file]\nnew_text: [replacement text - keep it concise, a few lines max]\nfile: [required - relative path from sandbox root, e.g. research/my-doc.md or state/goals.md]\n```\n\"@"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":97725,"output":1229,"cacheRead":13714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112668,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279455746}}
{"type":"message","id":"c074f7a9","parentId":"d1c05fab","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:24:42.045Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_kzid3mhbvkdh_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  81 # Re-read files post-mutation\n  82 $goals   = if (Test-Path $goalsFile) { Get-Content $goalsFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n  83 $pending = if (Test-Path $pendingFile) { Get-Content $pendingFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n  84 \n+ 85 # Sanitize text — replace curly quotes and em-dashes with ASCII equivalents for LLM compatibility\n+ 86 function Normalize-Text($t) {\n+ 87     if (-not $t) { return \"\" }\n+ 88     $t = $t -replace [char]0x2019, \"'\"   # right single quote\n+ 89     $t = $t -replace [char]0x2018, \"'\"   # left single quote\n+ 90     $t = $t -replace [char]0x201C, '\"'   # left double quote\n+ 91     $t = $t -replace [char]0x201D, '\"'   # right double quote\n+ 92     $t = $t -replace [char]0x2014, '-'  # em dash\n+ 93     $t = $t -replace [char]0x2013, '-'  # en dash\n+ 94     $t = $t -replace [char]0x03BB, \"λ\"  # Greek lambda — keep as-is but ensure UTF8\n+ 95     return $t\n+ 96 }\n+ 97 \n  85 # LLM call\n  86 $apiKey = $LLMApiKey\n  87 if (-not $apiKey) {\n  88     $keyFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\.llm_key\"\n  89     if (Test-Path $keyFile) { $apiKey = Get-Content $keyFile -Raw }\n  90 }\n  91 \n  92 $appliedInfo = if ($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Just applied: $($appliedMutations -join ', ')\" } else { \"No mutations applied this cycle.\" }\n  93 \n  94 $llmPrompt = @\"\n- 95 You are Breakaway — stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction.\n+108 You are Breakaway - stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction.\n  96 Your job: ONE concrete action that advances your goals. Be specific. Prefer file edits.\n  97 \n  98 Goals:\n- 99 $goals\n+112 $(Normalize-Text $goals)\n 100 \n