{"type":"message","id":"2231375d","parentId":"c074f7a9","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:24:53.135Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to also fix the LLM API call to properly handle the JSON encoding. The issue was that `ConvertTo-Json -Compress` might corrupt Unicode. Let me also check if the encoding is handled correctly. Let me look at the LLM call section.","thinkingSignature":"f2b027cf56ac0206fba5cf106430140fac48e0b20291abeb9dfddc581050415a"},{"type":"text","text":"\nNow fix the API call to use UTF-8 encoding properly:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_besuclnjj85t_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":110,"limit":50,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":98406,"output":130,"cacheRead":13714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112250,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279482048}}
{"type":"message","id":"ac4a2b1c","parentId":"2231375d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:24:53.182Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_besuclnjj85t_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\nGoals:\n$(Normalize-Text $goals)\n\nPending:\n$(Normalize-Text $pending)\n\nRecent: $recentPulseSummary\n\n$appliedInfo\n\nReply with exactly this format at the end. IMPORTANT: you MUST include the file: line in MUTATION - it is required.\n\n### OBSERVATION\n[1-2 sentence observation]\n\n### ACTION\n[Describe the file edit concisely]\n\n### MUTATION\n```\nold_text: [exact text to find - or \"(new file)\" if creating new file]\nnew_text: [replacement text - keep it concise, a few lines max]\nfile: [required - relative path from sandbox root, e.g. research/my-doc.md or state/goals.md]\n```\n\"@\n\n$llmResponse = \"\"\nif ($apiKey) {\n    $headers = @{\n        \"Authorization\" = \"Bearer $apiKey\"\n        \"Content-Type\" = \"application/json\"\n    }\n    $body = @{\n        model = $LLMModel\n        max_tokens = 1200\n        messages = @(@{role = \"user\"; content = $llmPrompt})\n    } | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5\n    try {\n        $resp = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\" -Method Post -Headers $headers -Body $body -TimeoutSec 60\n        Write-Host \"[DEBUG] resp keys: $($resp.PSObject.Properties.Name -join ', ')\"\n        $choices = $resp.choices\n        $choice0 = $null\n        if ($null -ne $choices -and $choices.Count -gt 0) { $choice0 = $choices[0] }\n        if ($null -ne $choice0) {\n            $rawContent = $choice0.message.content\n            if ($null -eq $rawContent) {\n                Write-Host \"[DEBUG] content is NULL. Full choice: $($choice0 | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 3)\"\n                $llmResponse = \"\"\n            } else {\n\n[94 more lines in file. Use offset=160 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774279493168}}
{"type":"message","id":"f3c0bb23","parentId":"ac4a2b1c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:25:08.540Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that `ConvertTo-Json` without `-Compress` might handle Unicode better, but the real issue was that the here-string had Unicode chars that were getting corrupted when embedded in the JSON. Now that I've normalized the text, the prompt should be clean ASCII.\n\nBut there's another issue: the `ConvertTo-Json` might not preserve UTF-8 properly for the Unicode characters that ARE valid (like λ). Let me change it to use UTF-8 encoding explicitly.\n\nActually, the issue is more subtle. When you use a here-string `@\"...\"@` in PowerShell with Unicode characters, and then pipe through `ConvertTo-Json`, the JSON serializer might escape them as `\\uXXXX`. \n\nWhen those escape sequences reach the API as string literals, the server might not decode them properly. The `\\u2014` for the em-dash is technically valid JSON, but if the server is using a simple char-by-char parser rather than a proper JSON decoder, it could fail on the backslash. My normalization approach of replacing the em-dash with a regular hyphen is the right call—it avoids the encoding issue entirely. I should also make sure `ConvertTo-Json` isn't compressing the output in a way that breaks the Unicode handling.","thinkingSignature":"50eb050f769714fafd7be4dbc3d42b825456407e2b8951bccbf423b30c751e92"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_s6xykmbke4jz_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1","oldText":"    $body = @{\n        model = $LLMModel\n        max_tokens = 1200\n        messages = @(@{role = \"user\"; content = $llmPrompt})\n    } | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5","newText":"    $body = @{\n        model = $LLMModel\n        max_tokens = 1200\n        messages = @(@{role = \"user\"; content = $llmPrompt})\n    }\n    $bodyJson = [System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8.GetBytes(($body | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5 -Compress))\n    $resp = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\" -Method Post -Headers $headers -Body $bodyJson -TimeoutSec 60"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":98543,"output":482,"cacheRead":13714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112739,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279493184}}
