{"type":"message","id":"a3e2d686","parentId":"8fb2a58d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:26:34.716Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait - the API key format is `sk-cp-...`. This looks like an OpenAI API key, not a MiniMax API key. But the MiniMax API accepts OpenAI-format keys for their OpenAI-compatible endpoint. So the key should work.\n\nLet me also think - when I called with `Invoke-RestMethod` before (earlier today with MiniMax-M2.7), I got `choices: [{finish_reason: length, index: 0, message: {}}]`. With `max_tokens = 200` and a simple prompt. The content was empty.\n\nMaybe the issue is that `sk-cp-boO3RF_KHio6...` is actually an MiniMax API key in OpenAI format. \n\nBut it's returning empty completions. Let me check the API base URL - I'm using `https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions`, which is MiniMax's endpoint. That should be correct. Let me try switching to `MiniMax-Abab` instead, since that might be what's actually available.\n\nWait, the response shows `\"model\": \"MiniMax-M2.7\"` which means the model parameter is being recognized. But I'm still getting empty content. Could it be that this particular API key doesn't have permissions for text generation? Or maybe `MiniMax-M2.7` requires a specific endpoint format like `https://api.minimax.io/v1/text/chatcompletion_v2`?\n\nI should try a higher `max_tokens` value - maybe 200 is too low and the model is hitting that limit immediately. But even with my simple test prompt, I'm getting empty content, so let me just test the MiniMax-M2.5 model instead to see if that works better.","thinkingSignature":"1d01a5fdd5741eb7984e0d01fa7732e712d839fa01c0328d151bc7f522c517ed"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1272m5cla8jh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"powershell -File \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\debug_llm.ps1\" 2>&1","yieldMs":25000,"timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":93440