{"type":"message","id":"ba6091c1","parentId":"e05be8b9","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:26:59.499Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait - that's just my response appearing in the output. The tool output shows the debug script ran and returned `\"Content length: 0\"`. So the LLM is returning empty content.\n\nThis is very strange. Let me try a different approach - maybe the issue is with the `model` name or the API endpoint. Let me try different models.\n\nActually, wait. Looking at the output more carefully, the `Content length: 0` means the script ran but the content was empty. So the MiniMax-M2.7 model is returning empty completions with ANY prompt.\n\nThis might be because:\n1. The API key is for a different model\n\n\n2. The API endpoint has changed\n3. The model is experiencing issues\n\nLet me check what other model names are available and try a few alternatives. Actually, I recall that earlier today when I made the exact same API call, it returned empty content too. So this is a persistent issue. The sandbox has been running this way for a while, which explains why no mutations have been generated - the LLM simply isn't producing any output. The empty completions mean the mutation generation is completely broken.\n\nLet me try the MiniMax API directly with the correct endpoint format instead of the OpenAI-compatible one.","thinkingSignature":"5bb263861b1662e7254bac7ea62c77c4f8772ef0374b4e83daabed97f51331b3"},{"type":"text","text":"MiniMax-M2.7 is returning empty completions for all prompts — the sandbox has been silently failing. Let me check if there's a different endpoint or model that works:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m3mgi3k99bvn_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\debug_llm2.ps1","content":"$apiKey = Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\.llm_key\" -Raw\n\n$headers = @{\n    \"Authorization\" = \"Bearer $apiKey\"\n    \"Content-Type\" = \"application/json\"\n}\n\n# Try different endpoints and models\n$tests = @(\n    @{ name = \"M2.7 via minimax-io\"; url = \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\"; model = \"MiniMax-M2.7\"; max_tokens = 100 },\n    @{ name = \"M2.7 via MiniMax-group\"; url = \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\"; model = \"MiniMax-M2.7\"; max_tokens = 100 },\n    @{ name = \"abab6.5s-chat\"; url = \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\"; model = \"abab6.5s-chat\"; max_tokens = 100 },\n    @{ name = \"MoE via MiniMax\"; url = \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\"; model = \"mini-hello\"; max_tokens = 50 }\n)\n\nforeach ($test in $tests) {\n    $body = @{\n        model = $test.model\n        max_tokens = $test.max_tokens\n        messages = @(@{role = \"user\"; content = \"Say hi\"})\n    } | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 3\n\n    try {\n        $resp = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri $test.url -Method POST -Headers $headers -Body ([System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8.GetBytes($body)) -TimeoutSec 15\n        $content = $resp.choices[0].message.content\n        $finish = $resp.choices[0].finish_reason\n        Write-Host \"[$($test.name)] content='$content' finish=$finish\"\n    } catch {\n        Write-Host \"[$($test.name)] ERROR: $($_.Exception.Message.Substring(0, [Math]::Min(100, $_.Exception.Message.Length)))\"\n    }\n}\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":94016,"output":783,"cacheRead":13714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108513,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279602698}}
