{"type":"message","id":"f4907a33","parentId":"f726e1bb","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:27:06.965Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I should check what the openclaw config uses for MiniMax. Let me also look at what model is being used by the main agent (MiniMax-M2.7) and see if it works differently there.Actually, looking at the situation:\n1. The main OpenClaw session works fine with `minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7`\n2. The sandbox `.llm_key` has `sk-cp-...` which is an OpenAI-format key\n3. The sandbox calls `https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions`\n\nBut OpenClaw uses `minimax-portal` as the provider. \n\nSo the portal has its own key separate from the sandbox key, which means the sandbox key might be misconfigured or have no available credits. Let me check if I can access the account info endpoint to see what's actually happening.","thinkingSignature":"2e91da6a36e6ed11d61db1fe4b3eda1780c98fde40a83de52eb45d143ce8d770"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ylfbap6no266_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"powershell -File \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\debug_llm2.ps1\" 2>&1","yieldMs":55000,"timeout":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":94839,"output":256,"cacheRead":13714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108809,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279619543}}
