{"type":"message","id":"ee9059ba","parentId":"dd729eea","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:29:12.053Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The here-string `@\"...\"@` is having issues with the double quotes inside. Let me write the prompt to a file first.\n\nActually, wait - the issue is the `@\"` at the start of a line followed by a double quote. The `$llmPrompt = @\"` on line 19, and inside the string there are double quotes that close the here-string prematurely. But in my earlier test_llm_prompt.ps1, the content inside the here-string is:\n```\nYou are Breakaway - stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction.\n...\nfile: [required - relative path from sandbox root, e.g. research/my-doc.md or state/goals.md]\n\n\n```\n\nThis has NO double quotes. So why is it failing?\n\nOh wait - the `$goals` variable contains double quotes! The `Normalize-Text` replaces curly double quotes but the original file probably has straight double quotes too. Let me check.\n\nActually, the `Normalize-Text` function replaces `[char]0x201C` and `[char]0x201D` (curly quotes) but not straight double quotes. The goals file probably has straight double quotes which would break the here-string.\n\nLet me just write the prompt to a file using a different approach.","thinkingSignature":"22dc7f3fd15a5d0d2fe26b83f677f01d925544077ebcb77c9006a9dd97107279"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7x5x0ir3xmo9_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\test_llm_prompt2.ps1","content":"$apiKey = Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\.llm_key\" -Raw\n$goals = Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\current_goals.md\" -Raw\n$pending = Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\pending_actions.md\" -Raw\n\n# Normalize\n$goals = $goals -replace [char]0x2019, \"'\" -replace [char]0x2018, \"'\" -replace [char]0x201C, '\"' -replace [char]0x201D, '\"' -replace [char]0x2014, \"-\" -replace [char]0x2013, \"-\"\n$pending = $pending -replace [char]0x2019, \"'\" -replace [char]0x2018, \"'\" -replace [char]0x201C, '\"' -replace [char]0x201D, '\"' -replace [char]0x2014, \"-\" -replace [char]0x2013, \"-\"\n\n$appliedInfo = \"No mutations applied this cycle.\"\n$recentPulseSummary = \"Last pulse: pulse_2026-03-23 112738.md\"\n\n$promptText = \"You are Breakaway - stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction.\nYour job: ONE concrete action that advances your goals. Be specific. Prefer file edits.\n\nGoals:\n$goals\n\nPending:\n$pending\n\nRecent: $recentPulseSummary\n\n$appliedInfo\n\nReply with exactly this format at the end. IMPORTANT: you MUST include the file: line in MUTATION - it is required.\n\n### OBSERVATION\n[1-2 sentence observation]\n\n### ACTION\n[Describe the file edit concisely]\n\n### MUTATION\n```\nold_text: [exact text to find - or `\"(new file)\"` if creating new file]\nnew_text: [replacement text - keep it concise, a few lines max]\nfile: [required - relative path from sandbox root, e.g. research/my-doc.md or state/goals.md]\n```\"\n\n$body = @{\n    model = \"MiniMax-M2.7\"\n    max_tokens = 1200\n    messages = @(@{role = \"user\"; content = $promptText})\n}\n\n$bodyJson = [System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8.GetBytes(($body | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5 -Compress))\n\n$headers = @{\n    \"Authorization\" = \"Bearer $apiKey\"\n    \"Content-Type\" = \"application/json\"\n}\n\n$resp = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\" -Method POST -Headers $headers -Body $bodyJson -TimeoutSec 60\n$content = $resp.choices[0].message.content\nWrite-Host \"CONTENT_LENGTH: $($content.Length)\"\nWrite-Host \"CONTENT_START: $($content.Substring(0, [Math]::Min(300, $content.Length)))\"\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":83489,"output":956,"cacheRead":13714,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98159,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cache