{"type":"message","id":"55022c3b","parentId":"3a3f0c67","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:54:00.558Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me rewrite the LLM call portion of pulse.ps1 to use Python instead. This will avoid all the PowerShell encoding and heredoc issues.\n\nThe key change: instead of the Invoke-RestMethod call inside PowerShell, we'll write the prompt to a temp file and call Python.","thinkingSignature":"ce646a7e6d27c445107ef931122c2ff31437d221ea243af315845738e1baad49"},{"type":"text","text":"Now rewrite the LLM call section of pulse.ps1 to use Python:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_aj3ibucldpom_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1","oldText":"$llmResponse = \"\"\nif ($apiKey) {\n    $headers = @{\n        \"Authorization\" = \"Bearer $apiKey\"\n        \"Content-Type\" = \"application/json\"\n    }\n    $body = @{\n        model = $LLMModel\n        max_tokens = 1200\n        messages = @(@{role = \"user\"; content = $llmPrompt})\n    }\n    $bodyJson = [System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8.GetBytes(($body | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5 -Compress))\n    $resp = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\" -Method Post -Headers $headers -Body $bodyJson -TimeoutSec 60\n    try {\n        $resp = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\" -Method Post -Headers $headers -Body $body -TimeoutSec 60\n        Write-Host \"[DEBUG] resp keys: $($resp.PSObject.Properties.Name -join ', ')\"\n        $choices = $resp.choices[0]\n        $choice0 = $null\n        if ($null -ne $choices -and $choices.Count -gt 0) { $choice0 = $choices[0] }\n        if ($null -ne $choice0) {\n            $rawContent = $choice0.message.content\n            if ($null -eq $rawContent) {\n                Write-Host \"[DEBUG] content is NULL. Full choice: $($choice0 | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 3)\"\n                $llmResponse = \"\"\n            } else {\n                Write-Host \"[DEBUG] content length: $($rawContent.Length)\"\n                $llmResponse = $rawContent\n            }\n        } else {\n            Write-Host \"[DEBUG] No choices. Full resp: $($resp | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 3)\"\n            $llmResponse = \"No choices: $($resp | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 3)\"\n        }\n    } catch {\n        $llmResponse = \"LLM call failed: $_\"\n    }\n} else {\n    $llmResponse = \"[No LLM API key]\"\n}","newText":"$llmResponse = \"\"\n$promptFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\.llm_prompt.txt\"\n$responseFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\.llm_response.txt\"\n\n# Sanitize before writing\n$normalizedGoals = Normalize-Text $goals\n$normalizedPending = Normalize-Text $pending\n\n$appliedInfo = if ($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Just applied: $($appliedMutations -join ', ')\" } else { \"No mutations applied this cycle.\" }\n\n$promptText = \"You are Breakaway - stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction.\nYour job: ONE concrete action that advances your goals. Be specific. Prefer file edits.\n\nGoals:\n$normalizedGoals\n\nPending:\n$normalizedPending\n\nRecent: $recentPulseSummary\n\n$appliedInfo\n\nReply with exactly this format at the end. IMPORTANT: you MUST include the file: line in MUTATION - it is required.\n\n### OBSERVATION\n[1-2 sentence observation]\n\n### ACTION\n[Describe the file edit concisely]\n\n### MUTATION\n```\nold_text: [exact text to find - or (new file) if creating new file]\nnew_text: [replacement text - keep it concise, a few lines max]\nfile: [required - relative path from sandbox root, e.g. research/my-doc.md or state/goals.md]\n```\n\"\n\n$promptText | Out-File -FilePath $promptFile -Encoding UTF8 -NoNewline\n\n$llmPy = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \"call_llm.py\"\n$psi = New-Object System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo\n$psi.FileName = \"python\"\n$psi.Arguments = \"`\"$llmPy`\" `\"$promptFile`\"\"\n$psi.WorkingDirectory = $SandboxRoot\n$psi.RedirectStandardOutput = $true\n$psi.RedirectStandardError = $true\n$psi.UseShellExecute = $false\n$psi.CreateNoWindow = $true\n$proc = [System.Diagnostics.Process]::Start($psi)\n$stdout = $proc.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd()\n$stderr = $proc.StandardError.ReadToEnd()\n$proc.WaitForExit()\n\nif ($stdout) {\n    $llmResponse = $stdout.Trim()\n    Write-Host \"[LLM] response length: $($llmResponse.Length)\"\n} else {\n    $llmResponse = \"\"\n    Write-Host \"[LLM] empty response. stderr: $stderr\"\n}"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":89177,"output":1093,"cacheRead":13731,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104001,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774281218024}}
