{"type":"message","id":"66ad9a9b","parentId":"9bad0d4e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:54:28.050Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the exact text. Let me do a targeted replacement of the LLM call section. The heredoc uses `@\"...`@` which is a here-string. This creates a multiline string in PowerShell. The issue is that the LLM response contains `\"@` (the here-string terminator) which then prematurely terminates the response when embedded in a subsequent here-string.\n\nLet me replace the entire LLM call section with a clean Python subprocess approach.","thinkingSignature":"b0cae0133b68c24c346ecac6b0e2af8748ab29ec388625fc246cd81bf2e6fa65"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0hgo5d7hfs8t_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1","oldString":"$llmResponse = \"\"\nif ($apiKey) {\n    $headers = @{\n        \"Authorization\" = \"Bearer $apiKey\"\n        \"Content-Type\" = \"application/json\"\n    }\n    $body = @{\n        model = $LLMModel\n        max_tokens = 1200\n        messages = @(@{role = \"user\"; content = $llmPrompt})\n    }\n    $bodyJson = [System.Text.Encoding]::UTF8.GetBytes(($body | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5 -Compress))\n    $resp = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\" -Method Post -Headers $headers -Body $bodyJson -TimeoutSec 60\n    try {\n        $resp = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\" -Method Post -Headers $headers -Body $body -TimeoutSec 60\n        Write-Host \"[DEBUG] resp keys: $($resp.PSObject.Properties.Name -join ', ')\"\n        $choices = $resp.choices\n        $choice0 = $null\n        if ($null -ne $choices -and $choices.Count -gt 0) { $choice0 = $choices[0] }\n        if ($null -ne $choice0) {\n            $rawContent = $choice0.message.content\n            if ($null -eq $rawContent) {\n                Write-Host \"[DEBUG] content is NULL. Full choice: $($choice0 | Conv