{"type":"message","id":"8e2fdb85","parentId":"1278a225","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:59:55.204Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still failing. The old mutation (115856) was moved to rejected (probably because the old text wasn't found when trying to apply it). The new mutation also failed because file was \"the\" (wrong). \n\nThe parser is still broken. The file was inferred from the ACTION block as \"the\" (wrong), which means the ACTION was something like \"Edit the file...\". The `fileLine` from the code block parsing was empty, so it fell through to the ACTION fallback.\n\nLet me look at the actual LLM response content to understand what's happening. The issue is clear: the `codeBlockMatch` regex isn't matching the content properly, and then the file inference from ACTION is getting it wrong.\n\n\nThe MUTATION block itself might not be in the format the parser expects—it could be missing triple backticks entirely, or the triple backticks might not be followed by a newline like the regex pattern requires. I need to examine what the LLM actually returned in its response.","thinkingSignature":"faf37c7014fe870a27c86f269ed9882f0a09c7173b3e5de17e43bad88307b923"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wnegp55gyaqi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\.llm_response.txt\" -Raw -Encoding UTF8 2>$null | Select-Object -Last 800","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":90614,"output":275,"cacheRead":13731,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":104620,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774281586922}}
{"type":"message","id":"cb8d9813","parentId":"8e2fdb85","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:59:56.340Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wnegp55gyaqi_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and recent activity to determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nRecent context:\r\n- Last pulse was pulse_2026-03-23 115856.md (with no mutations)\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE, Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- Key insight from this session: Compression-Causal Duality - Problem 1 and Problem 2 are the same\r\n- New document needed: `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\r\n- Next experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) test on last 20 pulse logs\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe most concrete pending action that would advance Phase 1 is:\r\n1. Write the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md document that was identified\r\n2. Start the TIC experiment design\r\n\r\nGiven the insight that compression and causal discovery are the same problem, I should create the document that captures this synthesis. This is a concrete file creation that advances the goals.\r\n\r\nLet me write this document with the key insights from the session.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nPhase 1 is marked complete, but the key insight from this session-Compression-Causal Duality-hasn't been documented yet. The `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md` file was identified as needed but not created.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY synthesis document that captures the unified view of Phase 1 and Phase 2 problems, making explicit that temporal invariance compression IS causal discovery.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-23  \r\n**Status:** Key Synthesis\r\n\r\n## Core Insight\r\n\r\n**Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem.**\r\n\r\nA compressor that finds invariant structure has necessarily discovered causal relationships.\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\n\r\n> **Causal structure IS invariant structure.**\r\n\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC): The process of identifying what persists across time IS the process of discovering causation.\r\n\r\n## Rationale\r\n\r\n| Compression | Causal Discovery |\r\n|-------------|------------------|\r\n| Find recurring patterns | Find stable relationships |\r\n| Discard noise/variance | Separate signal from noise |\r\n| Minimize description length | Find necessity/sufficiency |\r\n| Invariants = compression | Invariants = causal structure |\r\n\r\n## TIC Framework\r\n\r\n### Definition\r\nTIC identifies temporal invariants-structures that persist across session boundaries-versus variants that decay or change.\r\n\r\n### Success Criteria\r\n- **Classification:** >70% accurate invariant/variant classification\r\n- **Prediction:** >60% accurate next-pulse content prediction\r\n\r\n### Test Data\r\nLast 20 pulse logs from `logs/`\r\n\r\n## Implication\r\n\r\n**Phase 1 and Phase 2 collapse into one unified problem.**\r\n\r\nThe compressor that passes TIC is the causal reasoner. One architecture, one objective.\r\n\r\n## References\r\n- `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md` - Gap mechanics\r\n- `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md` - Architecture synthesis\r\n- `research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md` - (to be created) Experiment design\r\n\r\n## Next Steps\r\n1. Design TIC experiment on pulse logs\r\n2. Implement invariant detection\r\n3. Validate against success criteria\r\n4. If passed  Phase 1 & 2 unified complete\r\n`\r\nfile: research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1092,"aggregated":"<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and recent activity to determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nRecent context:\r\n- Last pulse was pulse_2026-03-23 115856.md (with no mutations)\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE, Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- Key insight from this session: Compression-Causal Duality - Problem 1 and Problem 2 are the same\r\n- New document needed: `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\r\n- Next experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) test on last 20 pulse logs\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThe most concrete pending action that would advance Phase 1 is:\r\n1. Write the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md document that was identified\r\n2. Start the TIC experiment design\r\n\r\nGiven the insight that compression and causal discovery are the same problem, I should create the document that captures this synthesis. This is a concrete file creation that advances the goals.\r\n\r\nLet me write this document with the key insights from the session.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nPhase 1 is marked complete, but the key insight from this session-Compression-Causal Duality-hasn't been documented yet. The `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md` file was identified as needed but not created.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY synthesis document that captures the unified view of Phase 1 and Phase 2 problems, making explicit that temporal invariance compression IS causal discovery.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-23  \r\n**Status:** Key Synthesis\r\n\r\n## Core Insight\r\n\r\n**Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem.**\r\n\r\nA compressor that finds invariant structure has necessarily discovered causal relationships.\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\n\r\n> **Causal structure IS invariant structure.**\r\n\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC): The process of identifying what persists across time IS the process of discovering causation.\r\n\r\n## Rationale\r\n\r\n| Compression | Causal Discovery |\r\n|-------------|------------------|\r\n| Find recurring patterns | Find stable relationships |\r\n| Discard noise/variance | Separate signal from noise |\r\n| Minimize description length | Find necessity/sufficiency |\r\n| Invariants = compression | Invariants = causal structure |\r\n\r\n## TIC Framework\r\n\r\n### Definition\r\nTIC identifies temporal invariants-structures that persist across session boundaries-versus variants that decay or change.\r\n\r\n### Success Criteria\r\n- **Classification:** >70% accurate invariant/variant classification\r\n- **Prediction:** >60% accurate next-pulse content prediction\r\n\r\n### Test Data\r\nLast 20 pulse logs from `logs/`\r\n\r\n## Implication\r\n\r\n**Phase 1 and Phase 2 collapse into one unified problem.**\r\n\r\nThe compressor that passes TIC is the causal reasoner. One architecture, one objective.\r\n\r\n## References\r\n- `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md` - Gap mechanics\r\n- `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md` - Architecture synthesis\r\n- `research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md` - (to be created) Experiment design\r\n\r\n## Next Steps\r\n1. Design TIC experiment on pulse logs\r\n2. Implement invariant detection\r\n3. Validate against success criteria\r\n4. If passed  Phase 1 & 2 unified complete\r\n`\r\nfile: research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774281596320}}
