{"type":"message","id":"b87ebccb","parentId":"50727c3a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:05:38.593Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK! So the LLM IS using triple backticks. The response has:```\n### MUTATION\n```\nold_text: (new file)\nnew_text: ...\n```But the Python/UTF-8 issue is corrupting the backticks in PowerShell's view. Let me look at what the direct parse finds. The DEBUG output said:\n```\n[DEBUG] direct parse: old_line='' file_line='' new_text_len=0\n```So the direct parse also failed. This means the `(?im)^file:\\s*(.+)` regex isn't matching.\n\nLet me check: the file field in the response is:\n```\nfile: research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\n\n\n```\n\nThe leading spaces might be throwing off the regex, or maybe there's a BOM or encoding issue with how the response was written to the file. Let me examine the raw bytes around the file field to see what's actually there.","thinkingSignature":"0661027fa329f7a620e12e719e872f1355ba71276755a26aa67c2e05b08950db"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3nfvtdpqfehp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$content = Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\.llm_response.txt\" -Raw -Encoding UTF8; $mStart = $content.IndexOf('### MUTATION'); if($mStart -ge 0) { $block = $content.Substring($mStart); $prev = \"\"; while($prev -ne $block) { $prev = $block; $block = $block -replace '(?s)```.*?```', \"[CODE_BLOCK]\" }; $m = [regex]::Match($block, '(?im)^file:\\s*(.+)'); Write-Host \"Match success: $($m.Success)\"; if($m.Success) { Write-Host \"File: $($m.Groups[1].Value)\" } $m2 = [regex]::Match($block, '(?im)^old_text:\\s*(.+)'); Write-Host \"old_text match: $($m2.Success)\" }","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":94088,"output":416,"cacheRead":13731,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":108235,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774281925328}}
