{"type":"message","id":"1d4bfc1f","parentId":"4a184db7","timestamp":"2026-03-23T16:06:44.642Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the triple backticks ARE present (`'### MUTATION\\n```\\nold_text: (new file)'`). The content looks correct. The issue is with the PowerShell regex matching. The problem might be that in PowerShell, when we read the file with `Get-Content -Raw -Encoding UTF8`, PowerShell is somehow corrupting the content.\n\nLet me try reading the file directly in Python and matching the regex there to see if it works.","thinkingSignature":"0779149a98da3a8018b574bbeffd94cfe495da6472add736958233119a6f5b6e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3rnbl51j3d4b_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\test_regex2.py","content":"import re, sys\nsys.stdout.reconfigure(encoding='utf-8')\n\nwith open(r\"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\.llm_response.txt\", \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\nmstart = content.find(\"### MUTATION\")\nif mstart >= 0:\n    block = content[mstart:]\n    print(f\"Block length: {len(block)}\")\n    \n    # Try triple backtick match\n    cb_match = re.search(r'(?s)```\\s*\\n(.*?)\\n```', block)\n    if cb_match:\n        print(f\"Triple backtick match: {len(cb_match.group(1))} chars\")\n    else:\n        print(\"Triple backtick match FAILED\")\n        # Try single backtick\n        cb_match2 = re.search(r'(?s)`\\s*\\n(.*?)\\n`', block)\n        if cb_match2:\n            print(f\"Single backtick match: {len(cb_match2.group(1))} chars\")\n        else:\n            print(\"Single backtick match FAILED\")\n            # Show what's around MUTATION\n            print(f\"Chars around MUTATION: {repr(block[:30])}\")\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":94932,"output":408,"cacheRead":13731,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109071,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cache