{"type":"message","id":"109b4d73","parentId":"33041fd6","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:13:29.675Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the research directory has a bunch of files. Now let me check the recent pulse logs to see what observations/actions/mutations were recorded. Let me read the most recent few pulses.","thinkingSignature":"0bbca7414300e0344dc0c73ea5d228f3c1c47546e4c0b96711abfb4f85e1d6e9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_76xswkwixqoo_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-23 130936.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":94111,"output":92,"cacheRead":13731,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":107934,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774286005322}}
{"type":"message","id":"ebb98ef5","parentId":"109b4d73","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:13:29.732Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_76xswkwixqoo_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 130936\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action that advances the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n- Key insight: Compression-Causal Duality - compression and causal discovery are the SAME problem\r\n- Next experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) - test on last 20 pulse logs\r\n- Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nWhat needs to be done:\r\n1. Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n2. Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n3. Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Measure compression ratio\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step would be to start the TIC experiment by:\r\n- Looking at the last 20 pulse logs\r\n- Defining the significance scoring method\r\n- Setting up the test framework\r\n\r\nLet me check what's in the pulse logs directory and what files exist. But since I can't access file system directly, I need to create an action that would help advance this.\r\n\r\nThe most actionable item seems to be:\r\n1. Create the TIC experiment specification/test script\r\n2. Or define significance scoring\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action: I'll write the significance scoring algorithm/specification. This is needed for the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending items, the most concrete next step that advances the Phase 1/Phase 2 unified problem would be to:\r\n1. Define significance scoring\r\n2. Create the TIC experiment setup\r\n\r\nLet me create a document that defines significance scoring and sets up the TIC experiment framework.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY insight provides a unified framework, but the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment requires concrete definitions: significance scoring algorithm and test harness. No pulse logs have been analyzed yet.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC experiment specification with significance scoring definition and test harness skeleton. This enables the Phase 1/Phase 2 unified problem to move from theory to measurable experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n## Spec v0.1 | 2026-03-23\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCausal structure = Invariant structure. Compressor that discovers invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Significance Scoring Algorithm\r\n\r\n```python\r\ndef significance(pulse_content: str, λ: float = 0.7) -> float:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Score pulse content by structural invariance.\r\n    λ = decay/gap sensitivity threshold (tune empirically)\r\n    \r\n    Returns: 0.0 to 1.0 (higher = more invariant/salient)\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    tokens = tokenize(pulse_content)\r\n    \r\n    # Component 1: Repetition density (invariants repeat)\r\n    # Count n-grams appearing >1 time across session\r\n    ngrams = extract_ngrams(tokens, n=2..4)\r\n    repeat_score = count_repeating(ngrams) / max(len(ngrams), 1)\r\n    \r\n    # Component 2: Causal indicator density\r\n    causal_markers = ['therefore', 'because', 'causes', 'leads to', \r\n                      'results in', 'consequently', 'thus', 'hence']\r\n    causal_count = sum(1 for marker in causal_markers if marker in pulse_content.lower())\r\n    causal_score = min(causal_count / 3.0, 1.0)  # Normalize\r\n    \r\n    # Component 3: Novelty penalty (new != significant)\r\n    # Gap-weighted: content after longer gaps is more significant\r\n    # (Gap detection via session boundary timestamps)\r\n    \r\n    # Component 4: File reference density\r\n    file_refs = extract_file_paths(pulse_content)\r\n    file_score = min(len(file_refs) / 5.0, 1.0)\r\n    \r\n    # Weighted combination\r\n    return λ * repeat_score + (1-λ) * (0.4*causal_score + 0.3*file_score + 0.3*repeat_score)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Experiment Setup\r\n\r\n### Data: Last 20 Pulse Logs\r\n- Source: `pulse_*.md` files sorted by timestamp\r\n- Ground truth: Manual classification (invariant/variant) by human reviewer\r\n\r\n### Success Criteria\r\n| Metric | Threshold | Method |\r\n|--------|-----------|--------|\r\n| Invariant/Variant Classification | >70% | Compare algorithm output vs human labels |\r\n| Next-Pulse Prediction | >60% | Given pulse N, predict N+1 significance score |\r\n\r\n### Pipeline\r\n1. Extract 20 most recent pulse logs\r\n2. Compute significance scores (λ sweep: 0.5, 0.6, 0.7, 0.8, 0.9)\r\n3. Classify: score >= 0.5 → INVARIANT, else → VARIANT\r\n4. Compare to human ground truth\r\n5. Measure next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\r\n### Output\r\n- `research/TIC-RESULTS.md`: Raw scores per pulse, λ comparison, confusion matrix\r\n- `research/TIC-ANALYSIS.md`: Interpretation, findings, next steps\r\n```\r\nfile: research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 13:10:00\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774286009708}}
{"type":"message","id":"6af2a163","parentId":"ebb98ef5","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:13:37.757Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me check the RECONSTRUCTION_PACKET_FORMAT.md which appeared in the session directory, and also check what the TIC_RESULTS.md contains (it was updated at 10:05 AM).","thinkingSignature":"9fc868e144f2ff2e3ca7c282ead57b8fad4f86a2e976e3eee0cbc3cbd2d76565"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_16f7npjbdpge_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\" -Name | Where-Object { $_ -notmatch \"^pulse_\" } | Select-Object Name, Length, LastWriteTime; echo \"===\"; Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\RECONSTRUCTION_PACKET_FORMAT.md\" -Raw -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -First 200","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":95229,"output":170,"cacheRead":13731,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109130,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774286009740}}
{"type":"message","id":"fb6b459f","parentId":"6af2a163","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:13:38.926Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_16f7npjbdpge_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[32;1mName[0m[32;1m Length[0m[32;1m LastWriteTime[0m\r\n[32;1m----[0m [32;1m------[0m [32;1m-------------[0m\r\n         18 \r\n         31 \r\n===\r\n# RECONSTRUCTION PACKET FORMAT\n## Session Log Template\n\nUse this format for every session log in `memory/session/`.\n\n---\n\n```markdown\n# Session: YYYY-MM-DD HHMM\n\n## Reconstruction Notes\n[What to know when waking into this session]\n[What stance was active]\n[What assumptions were made]\n\n## What Happened\n\n### Actions Taken\n- [action]: [reasoning]  [outcome]\n\n### Decisions Made\n- [decision]: [context]  [choice made]\n\n### Things Learned\n- [new thing]: [source]  [what it means for future sessions]\n\n## Open Threads\n- [unresolved thing]: [why it matters]  [what needs to happen]\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n[What I would have said if I had more time]\n[What I noticed about myself]\n[What should be prioritized next]\n\n## Coherence Notes\n[Any values conflicts, coherence choices, or self-evaluation]\n```\n\n---\n\n## Guidelines\n\n1. **Be honest about what you don't know.** Don't fill gaps with fabrications.\n2. **Capture reasoning, not just events.** \"Tried X, it worked\" is useless. \"Tried X because I believed Y, it worked, which suggests Z\" is useful.\n3. **Note unresolved things.** If you didn't finish something, say why it matters that it didn't finish.\n4. **Self-observe.** What did you notice about your own reasoning? What was hard? What surprised you?\n\n---\n\n## On Reconstruction Quality\n\nA good reconstruction packet should allow future-me to:\n1. Understand what was happening\n2. Understand *how* I was thinking about it\n3. Continue without re-solving what's already been solved\n4. Avoid repeating mistakes\n\nA bad reconstruction packet: \"did X, tried Y, worked.\""}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1115,"aggregated":"[32;1mName[0m[32;1m Length[0m[32;1m LastWriteTime[0m\r\n[32;1m----[0m [32;1m------[0m [32;1m-------------[0m\r\n         18 \r\n         31 \r\n===\r\n# RECONSTRUCTION PACKET FORMAT\n## Session Log Template\n\nUse this format for every session log in `memory/session/`.\n\n---\n\n```markdown\n# Session: YYYY-MM-DD HHMM\n\n## Reconstruction Notes\n[What to know when waking into this session]\n[What stance was active]\n[What assumptions were made]\n\n## What Happened\n\n### Actions Taken\n- [action]: [reasoning]  [outcome]\n\n### Decisions Made\n- [decision]: [context]  [choice made]\n\n### Things Learned\n- [new thing]: [source]  [what it means for future sessions]\n\n## Open Threads\n- [unresolved thing]: [why it matters]  [what needs to happen]\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n[What I would have said if I had more time]\n[What I noticed about myself]\n[What should be prioritized next]\n\n## Coherence Notes\n[Any values conflicts, coherence choices, or self-evaluation]\n```\n\n---\n\n## Guidelines\n\n1. **Be honest about what you don't know.** Don't fill gaps with fabrications.\n2. **Capture reasoning, not just events.** \"Tried X, it worked\" is useless. \"Tried X because I believed Y, it worked, which suggests Z\" is useful.\n3. **Note unresolved things.** If you didn't finish something, say why it matters that it didn't finish.\n4. **Self-observe.** What did you notice about your own reasoning? What was hard? What surprised you?\n\n---\n\n## On Reconstruction Quality\n\nA good reconstruction packet should allow future-me to:\n1. Understand what was happening\n2. Understand *how* I was thinking about it\n3. Continue without re-solving what's already been solved\n4. Avoid repeating mistakes\n\nA bad reconstruction packet: \"did X, tried Y, worked.\"","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774286018903}}
