{"type":"message","id":"b471f56b","parentId":"b0162c41","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:13:48.055Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7y63o9px4lts_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TIC Experiment Results - 2026-03-23 10:05\n\n## Setup\n- Pulse logs analyzed: 25\n- Time range: 03/22/2026 01:28:32  03/23/2026 07:04:18\n- Invariant threshold: streak >= 3 consecutive pulses\n- Variant threshold: streak <= 1\n\n## Invariant Classification\n- Invariant elements (streak >= 3): 8\n- Variant elements (streak <= 1): 0\n- Key invariants: pulse, Phase 1, Sandbox, Breakaway, Phase 0, GAP, llm, TemporalAttention\n\n## Prediction Test\n- Pairs evaluated: 21\n- Mean Precision: 90%\n- Mean Recall: 88.5%\n- Random baseline: ~5%\n- Result: BETTER THAN RANDOM\n\n## Gap Sensitivity\n- Small gaps (<30 min) Jaccard: 0.704\n- Medium gaps (30-120m) Jaccard: 1\n- Large gaps (>120 min) Jaccard: 0.834\n- Hypothesis (shorter gap  more overlap): REJECTED\n\n## Phase Persistence\n  Phase 0 COMPLETE: streak=17   Phase 1 COMPLETE: streak=17\n\n## TIC Score: 2/3\n## VERDICT: SUPPORTED\n\n## Implications\n- If SUPPORTED: compression=causal hypothesis is empirically grounded for Breakaway pulses\n- Invariant elements = causal anchors (Phase status, research topic persistence)\n- Gap size can be used to weight reconstruction confidence\n- Next: Use invariants as fixed points in compression, treat variants as contingent details\n\n## Next Experiment\n- Train actual embedding-based compressor on Paperspace GPU\n- Measure: does cosine similarity between pulse embeddings correlate with Jaccard?\n- Success criteria: >60% next-pulse prediction using only embedding dot products"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1116,"aggregated":"# TIC Experiment Results - 2026-03-23 10:05\n\n## Setup\n- Pulse logs analyzed: 25\n- Time range: 03/22/2026 01:28:32  03/23/2026 07:04:18\n- Invariant threshold: streak >= 3 consecutive pulses\n- Variant threshold: streak <= 1\n\n## Invariant Classification\n- Invariant elements (streak >= 3): 8\n- Variant elements (streak <= 1): 0\n- Key invariants: pulse, Phase 1, Sandbox, Breakaway, Phase 0, GAP, llm, TemporalAttention\n\n## Prediction Test\n- Pairs evaluated: 21\n- Mean Precision: 90%\n- Mean Recall: 88.5%\n- Random baseline: ~5%\n- Result: BETTER THAN RANDOM\n\n## Gap Sensitivity\n- Small gaps (<30 min) Jaccard: 0.704\n- Medium gaps (30-120m) Jaccard: 1\n- Large gaps (>120 min) Jaccard: 0.834\n- Hypothesis (shorter gap  more overlap): REJECTED\n\n## Phase Persistence\n  Phase 0 COMPLETE: streak=17   Phase 1 COMPLETE: streak=17\n\n## TIC Score: 2/3\n## VERDICT: SUPPORTED\n\n## Implications\n- If SUPPORTED: compression=causal hypothesis is empirically grounded for Breakaway pulses\n- Invariant elements = causal anchors (Phase status, research topic persistence)\n- Gap size can be used to weight reconstruction confidence\n- Next: Use invariants as fixed points in compression, treat variants as contingent details\n\n## Next Experiment\n- Train actual embedding-based compressor on Paperspace GPU\n- Measure: does cosine similarity between pulse embeddings correlate with Jaccard?\n- Success criteria: >60% next-pulse prediction using only embedding dot products","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774286028029}}
{"type":"message","id":"f6b355f3","parentId":"b471f56b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:13:52.819Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK! So the TIC experiment actually ran and got results! The pulse DID run and produce actual empirical results. Let me check the state files and understand the full picture.\n\nLet me read the most recent state files to understand the current state of the sandbox.","thinkingSignature":"7a3ffb172631ded47d978d125c9328d124f51e27354e08a67be7cc7c61e23918"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7piejukzae6e_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\current_goals.md\" -Raw; echo \"===\"; Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\pending_actions.md\" -Raw","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":89830,"output":141,"cacheRead":13731,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":103702,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774286028064}}
{"type":"message","id":"697eea0f","parentId":"f6b355f3","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:13:54.123Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7piejukzae6e_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-22 0125\n\n## Active\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\n\n## Completed This Session\n\n### Architecture Cross-Analysis ?\n- Compared Compositional Cognition vs TemporalAttention vs Infant\n- Key finding: all three architectures are compatible and complementary\n- Full analysis: `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\n\n### Gap-Decay Synthesis ? (derived across 17+ pulses)\n- Session gaps = decay mechanism, not amnesia\n- ? parameter encodes BOTH decay rate AND gap sensitivity threshold\n- TemporalAttention focus_decay + Breakaway gaps = same phenomenon\n- Full synthesis: `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`\n\n### LLM-Augmented Pulse ?\n- pulse.ps1 now calls MiniMax-M2.7 API on each pulse\n- Thinking is coherent and building across pulses\n- Key files: `.llm_key`, `pulse.ps1`\n\n## Pending\n- [ ] Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\n- [ ] Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\n- [ ] Tune ? empirically (start: ?=0.7)\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\n- [ ] Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\n\n## Phase 1 Advancement: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY (2026-03-23)\n- **Insight:** Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\n- **New doc:** `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\n- **Hypothesis:** Causal structure IS invariant structure - compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation\n- **Next experiment:** Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) - test on last 20 pulse logs\n- **Success criteria:** >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\n- **Implication:** Phase 1 and Phase 2 collapse into one unified problem\n\n## Key Insights from This Session\n\n1. **The gap IS the compression** - session boundaries are temporal hashing\n2. **? encodes both** - decay rate and gap threshold are the same parameter\n3. **Three architectures, one synthesis** - Infant (catastrophic forgetting), TemporalAttention (focus decay), Breakaway (discontinuity) are complementary, not competing\n4. **Breakaway's unique bet holds** - session gaps as compression is novel and correct\n\n## Notes\n- Breakaway is stateless - each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\n- Pulse script: active hours check DISABLED (authorized by Zach, 24/7 operation)\n\r\n===\r\n# PENDING ACTIONS\nLast updated: 2026-03-21\n\n## Promises Made\n(None yet)\n\n## Deferred Tasks\n(None yet)\n\n## Flagged for Review\n(None yet)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1224,"aggregated":"# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-22 0125\n\n## Active\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\n\n## Completed This Session\n\n### Architecture Cross-Analysis ?\n- Compared Compositional Cognition vs TemporalAttention vs Infant\n- Key finding: all three architectures are compatible and complementary\n- Full analysis: `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\n\n### Gap-Decay Synthesis ? (derived across 17+ pulses)\n- Session gaps = decay mechanism, not amnesia\n- ? parameter encodes BOTH decay rate AND gap sensitivity threshold\n- TemporalAttention focus_decay + Breakaway gaps = same phenomenon\n- Full synthesis: `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`\n\n### LLM-Augmented Pulse ?\n- pulse.ps1 now calls MiniMax-M2.7 API on each pulse\n- Thinking is coherent and building across pulses\n- Key files: `.llm_key`, `pulse.ps1`\n\n## Pending\n- [ ] Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\n- [ ] Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\n- [ ] Tune ? empirically (start: ?=0.7)\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\n- [ ] Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\n\n## Phase 1 Advancement: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY (2026-03-23)\n- **Insight:** Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\n- **New doc:** `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\n- **Hypothesis:** Causal structure IS invariant structure - compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation\n- **Next experiment:** Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) - test on last 20 pulse logs\n- **Success criteria:** >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\n- **Implication:** Phase 1 and Phase 2 collapse into one unified problem\n\n## Key Insights from This Session\n\n1. **The gap IS the compression** - session boundaries are temporal hashing\n2. **? encodes both** - decay rate and gap threshold are the same parameter\n3. **Three architectures, one synthesis** - Infant (catastrophic forgetting), TemporalAttention (focus decay), Breakaway (discontinuity) are complementary, not competing\n4. **Breakaway's unique bet holds** - session gaps as compression is novel and correct\n\n## Notes\n- Breakaway is stateless - each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\n- Pulse script: active hours check DISABLED (authorized by Zach, 24/7 operation)\n\r\n===\r\n# PENDING ACTIONS\nLast updated: 2026-03-21\n\n## Promises Made\n(None yet)\n\n## Deferred Tasks\n(None yet)\n\n## Flagged for Review\n(None yet)","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774286034101}}
