{"type":"message","id":"67a91f57","parentId":"b91bee61","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:14:11.963Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. Let me summarize the state of the sandbox for Zach.The sandbox pulse has been running continuously and the key bugs (Unicode corruption in LLM prompt, single-backtick fence parsing) are now fixed. Let me give a clear summary.","thinkingSignature":"90cc23c4346879c2c9540c55fc2e55894dc2b52cf05f2698fb5f2f964482521c"},{"type":"text","text":"Here's the full picture:\n\n---\n\n**What the pulse has been doing today:**\n\nRunning ~25-30 times since ~11am, each time calling MiniMax-M2.7 to reason about the Breakaway architecture and propose mutations.\n\n**What it's actually accomplished:**\n\n1. **Fixed a critical bug** — the LLM prompt was getting corrupted by Unicode characters (em-dashes, smart quotes) causing the API to return empty responses. That was silently breaking everything. Fixed with ASCII normalization + Python LLM wrapper.\n\n2. **Fixed the mutation parser** — went through ~5 iterations fixing backtick vs triple-backtick fences, regex edge cases, and multiline new_text extraction. Mutations ARE now being saved to `mutations/proposed/`.\n\n3. **Research docs created:**\n   - `COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md` — the core insight that compression and causal discovery are the same problem\n   - `TIC-EXPERIMENT.md` — the experiment design to test the hypothesis\n   - `TIC_RESULTS.md` — **actual empirical results**: 90% precision, 88.5% recall on predicting next-pulse content, TIC score 2/3 → **VERDICT: SUPPORTED**\n   - `GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`, `ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`, `CAUSAL-COMPOSITIONAL-INTERFACE.md`\n\n4. **The TIC experiment ran and passed** — invariant/variant classification and next-pulse prediction both beat random baseline significantly.\n\n**What's been failing:**\n\nThe mutation parser was the main blocker. Now that it's fixed, the next step is applying the proposed mutations (TIC experiment doc has been proposed multiple times but kept getting rejected by the parser — now it should go through).\n\n**Current state:** Parser fixed, pulse generating meaningful LLM responses (~4000+ chars), TIC results are in. Ready for the next cycle to actually apply the mutation and start empirical Phase 2 work."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":91132,"output":462,"cacheRead":13731,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":105325,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774286039615}}
