{"type":"message","id":"b338fe38","parentId":"60ad3d03","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:26:05.015Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, the issue is clear: the `block` variable has ALREADY been through the code fence removal loop. So the triple backticks have been replaced with `[CODE_BLOCK]`. By the time I try to find ` ``` ` it's already gone.\n\nThe fix is: extract the mutation block content from the ORIGINAL `$llmResponse` BEFORE the fence removal loop, not from the already-processed `$block`.\n\nLet me restructure the mutation parsing to:\n1. First, extract the raw MUTATION block from `$llmResponse` (before any processing)\n2. Then parse the key-value fields from it","thinkingSignature":"515bd5eb19c087aff77a0c9f22c7aba35b60146f3274ff2a92ecbc6880e5112b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mhro3jz4syd7_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":185,"limit":60,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":93301,"output":185,"cacheRead":13731,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":107217,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774286755663}}
