{"type":"message","id":"5bf10887","parentId":"c5ac6b9d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:41:04.975Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cd5ngjiakxia_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OK[31;1mDEBUG: old='(new file)'[0m\r\n[31;1mDEBUG: new_text len=1376, starts='# Derived from COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis (2026-0'[0m\r\n[31;1mDEBUG: file='research/SIGNIFICANCE-SCORING.md'[0m\r\n[31;1mResult written to C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\.mutation_parse_result.json[0m\r\n{\r\n  \"old\": \"(new file)\",\r\n  \"new\": \"# Derived from COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis (2026-03-23)\\n\\n## Core Hypothesis\\n> Significance = variance across sessions (what changes)\\n> Invariance = stability across sessions (what persists)\\n\\nA pulse segment is **significant** if its representation changes between sessions.\\nA pulse segment is **invariant** if its representation persists across sessions.\\n\\n## Significance Score Formula\\n\\n\\n\\nWhere:\\n- `v_prev` = embedding of segment at end of previous session\\n- `v_curr` = embedding of segment at start of current session\\n- � ? [0, 1]: 0 = fully invariant, 1 = fully significant\\n\\n## Operational Thresholds\\n\\n| Score Range | Classification | Interpretation |\\n|-------------|----------------|----------------|\\n| � < 0.2     | INVARIANT      | Compressed out (stable knowledge) |\\n| 0.2 � � < 0.6 | TRANSITIONAL | Retained, may decay |\\n| � � 0.6     | SIGNIFICANT    | New, worth encoding |\\n\\n## Derived: Causal Invariance Detection\\n\\nFor TIC experiment on last 20 pulse logs:\\n\\n1. Extract all substantive claims/updates per pulse\\n2. Compute � for each claim across consecutive sessions\\n3. Claims with � < 0.3 = invariant structure (causal)\\n4. Claims with � > 0.5 = episodic variance\\n\\n**Success target:** >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\\n\\n## Next\\n- [ ] Implement � scoring in pulse.ps1\\n- [ ] Run TIC on pulse_*.md logs\\n- [ ] Validate against manual classification\",\r\n  \"file\": \"research/SIGNIFICANCE-SCORING.md\"\r\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1409,"aggregated":"OK[31;1mDEBUG: old='(new file)'[0m\r\n[31;1mDEBUG: new_text len=1376, starts='# Derived from COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis (2026-0'[0m\r\n[31;1mDEBUG: file='research/SIGNIFICANCE-SCORING.md'[0m\r\n[31;1mResult written to C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\.mutation_parse_result.json[0m\r\n{\r\n  \"old\": \"(new file)\",\r\n  \"new\": \"# Derived from COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis (2026-03-23)\\n\\n## Core Hypothesis\\n> Significance = variance across sessions (what changes)\\n> Invariance = stability across sessions (what persists)\\n\\nA pulse segment is **significant** if its representation changes between sessions.\\nA pulse segment is **invariant** if its representation persists across sessions.\\n\\n## Significance Score Formula\\n\\n\\n\\nWhere:\\n- `v_prev` = embedding of segment at end of previous session\\n- `v_curr` = embedding of segment at start of current session\\n- � ? [0, 1]: 0 = fully invariant, 1 = fully significant\\n\\n## Operational Thresholds\\n\\n| Score Range | Classification | Interpretation |\\n|-------------|----------------|----------------|\\n| � < 0.2     | INVARIANT      | Compressed out (stable knowledge) |\\n| 0.2 � � < 0.6 | TRANSITIONAL | Retained, may decay |\\n| � � 0.6     | SIGNIFICANT    | New, worth encoding |\\n\\n## Derived: Causal Invariance Detection\\n\\nFor TIC experiment on last 20 pulse logs:\\n\\n1. Extract all substantive claims/updates per pulse\\n2. Compute � for each claim across consecutive sessions\\n3. Claims with � < 0.3 = invariant structure (causal)\\n4. Claims with � > 0.5 = episodic variance\\n\\n**Success target:** >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\\n\\n## Next\\n- [ ] Implement � scoring in pulse.ps1\\n- [ ] Run TIC on pulse_*.md logs\\n- [ ] Validate against manual classification\",\r\n  \"file\": \"research/SIGNIFICANCE-SCORING.md\"\r\n}","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774287664949}}
