{"type":"message","id":"633ba8e9","parentId":"d001023e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:45:21.390Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7hzzvmxs24fz_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n**Created:** 2026-03-23\n**Status:** IN PROGRESS\n\n## Hypothesis\nCausal structure = invariant structure. A compressor that discovers invariants has discovered causation.\n\n## Method\n1. Collect last 20 pulse logs\n2. Extract features from each pulse (file operations, goals, insights)\n3. Define invariance: features that persist across session gaps\n4. Define variance: features that change between sessions\n5. Train/test split: 15 training pulses, 5 test pulses\n6. Measure:\n   - Invariant/variant classification accuracy\n   - Next-pulse prediction accuracy\n\n## Success Criteria\n- >70% invariant/variant classification\n- >60% next-pulse prediction\n\n## Implementation Notes\n- Use existing pulse logs in `state/pulse_*.md`\n- Feature extraction: parse goals, actions, mutations per pulse\n- Invariance metric: ?-weighted overlap with prior pulse\n- ? start: 0.7 (as per pending tuning)\n\n## Next Steps\n- [ ] Extract features from pulse logs\n- [ ] Implement invariance scoring\n- [ ] Run classification experiment\n- [ ] Measure prediction accuracy\n- [ ] Tune ? based on results"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1066,"aggregated":"research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n**Created:** 2026-03-23\n**Status:** IN PROGRESS\n\n## Hypothesis\nCausal structure = invariant structure. A compressor that discovers invariants has discovered causation.\n\n## Method\n1. Collect last 20 pulse logs\n2. Extract features from each pulse (file operations, goals, insights)\n3. Define invariance: features that persist across session gaps\n4. Define variance: features that change between sessions\n5. Train/test split: 15 training pulses, 5 test pulses\n6. Measure:\n   - Invariant/variant classification accuracy\n   - Next-pulse prediction accuracy\n\n## Success Criteria\n- >70% invariant/variant classification\n- >60% next-pulse prediction\n\n## Implementation Notes\n- Use existing pulse logs in `state/pulse_*.md`\n- Feature extraction: parse goals, actions, mutations per pulse\n- Invariance metric: ?-weighted overlap with prior pulse\n- ? start: 0.7 (as per pending tuning)\n\n## Next Steps\n- [ ] Extract features from pulse logs\n- [ ] Implement invariance scoring\n- [ ] Run classification experiment\n- [ ] Measure prediction accuracy\n- [ ] Tune ? based on results","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774287921358}}
{"type":"message","id":"417c04ae","parentId":"633ba8e9","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:45:43.263Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is the same content as the previously applied mutation (2026-03-23 132919). The system is checking if the oldText matches something in the file. If the file already has this content, the `-replace` would do nothing (or the `[NEW_FILE]` check fails because the file exists with different content).\n\nLooking at the apply logic:```pwsh\nif ($isNewFile) {    $updated = $newText    ...\n    continue\n}\n$current = Get-Content $fullPath -Rawif ($current -notlike \"*$oldText*\") {\n    Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$($mfile.Name)\" -Force\n\n\n```\n\nThe rejection happens because the file already exists with the same content, so when I search for the `[NEW_FILE]` marker in it, the check fails and the mutation gets flagged as already applied.\n\nLooking at the actual rejection message, it says \"missing\" which refers to the file path not existing on disk. So the auto-apply system is rejecting mutations when the target file already contains that exact content.\n\nWait, that's not quite right either. If the file existed with identical content, the `[NEW_FILE]` check would fail to find the marker and it would be rejected for \"old text not found\" instead.\n\nThe real problem is that a file like `research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md` was created during the first mutation cycle, but now a second mutation trying to create the same file with the same content is being rejected because the file already exists.\n\n```\nOld approach: `Move-Item proposed → applied` no longer works\nNew approach: Apply the mutation content, but oldText matches existing content → no change → reject\n```\nThe system detects identical content and treats it as a duplicate mutation.\n\nActually, the correct behavior should be:\n1. If file exists and oldText == `[NEW_FILE]` and content is identical → skip (already applied, no change needed) → accept\n2. If file exists and oldText != `[NEW_FILE]` and oldText found → apply\n3. If file exists and oldText != `[NEW_FILE]` and oldText NOT found → reject\n4. If file exists and oldText == `[NEW_FILE]` but content different → this shouldn't happen for new files\n\nBut currently: case 1 → file exists with `[NEW_FILE]` but oldText not in file → reject\n\nThe fix for case 1: if `isNewFile` and file exists, accept it (it's already applied). Let me fix the apply logic.\n\nActually, looking at the code flow again — when `isNewFile = true`, the code sets `updated = newText` and writes it to the file, then moves the mutation to the applied folder. So even if the file already exists, it's overwriting it with the same content and accepting it. The rejection must be happening because the `oldText` doesn't match the file content, not because of the new file logic. Wait, I'm looking at the rejection reason: `\"$file (missing)\"`. This comes from the `$file -notlike \"*$oldText*\"` check. But for `[NEW_FILE]`, that check is skipped. So the rejection reason is from something else. Let me re-examine the code flow more carefully. I think the issue is that the `[NEW_FILE]` check happens first and sets `$file`, then the file existence check runs, but if the file exists and `isNewFile` is true, it gets written anyway without being rejected. So the rejection must be coming from a different path in the logic. I think the issue is that when a mutation comes in with `[NEW_FILE]` but the file already exists with identical content, the check `$current -notlike \"*$oldText*\"` fails because `oldText` is actually `[NEW_FILE]`, which isn't in the existing file—causing it to be rejected as \"missing\" when it should probably just be marked as already applied or superseded.","thinkingSignature":"2a1c446f31e345074dc180a8a48fc6cd13a3385e0b715e4be5ce95fbec231ede"},{"type":"text","text":"The system is rejecting the TIC-EXPERIMENT.md mutation because the file already exists with identical content. Need to fix the auto-apply to accept \"already applied\" mutations:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r05o7igm1uwf_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":48,"limit":45,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":98216,"output":916,"cacheRead":13731,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112863,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774287921402}}
{"type":"message","id":"237ded07","parentId":"417c04ae","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:45:43.315Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_r05o7igm1uwf_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        $fullPath = Join-Path $SandboxRoot $file\n        if (-not $fullPath.StartsWith($SandboxRoot)) {\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (unsafe path)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        if (-not (Test-Path $fullPath)) {\n            # New file case\n            if ($oldText -eq \"[NEW_FILE]\") {\n                $newText | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n                Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n                Write-Host \"[mutation applied] NEW FILE: $file\"\n                $appliedMutations += \"$file (new)\"\n                continue\n            }\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (missing)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        $current = Get-Content $fullPath -Raw\n        if ($current.Length -eq 0 -or $current -notmatch [regex]::Escape($oldText)) {\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (old text not found)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        # Use simple string Replace for multiline content (avoids regex OOM on large texts)\n        $updated = $current.Replace($oldText, $newText)\n        $updated | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n        Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n        Write-Host \"[mutation applied] $file\"\n        $appliedMutations += $file\n    }\n}\n\n# Re-read files post-mutation\n$goals   = if (Test-Path $goalsFile) { Get-Content $goalsFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n$pending = if (Test-Path $pendingFile) { Get-Content $pendingFile -Raw } else { \