{"type":"message","id":"9f211e65","parentId":"2cdac977","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:50:10.334Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue. The LLM is putting the MUTATION block content on a SINGLE LINE:\n```\n```\nold_text: (new file)new_text: # TIC: Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\n```\n\nThere's no newline between `old_text: (new file)` and `new_text:`. They're on the same \"line\" in the code block, separated by just a space. My parser uses `^old_text:\\s*(.+)` multiline which would match `old_text: (new file)new_text: # TIC...` as a single match because there's no newline.\n\nThe fix: in the `old_text` regex match, I should NOT capture `new_text:` as part of `old_text`. \n\nI could strip out `new_text:` content from the captured `old_text` value, but that feels hacky. A cleaner approach would be to match `old_text:` first, then handle `new_text:` and `file:` as separate patterns, rather than trying to parse everything with a single regex that assumes proper line breaks.\n\nLooking at the actual format, the real problem is that `old_text:` captures everything on that line—including `new_text:` that appears later. So when I capture `(.+)` for `old_text`, it's greedily taking `old_text: (new file)new_text: # TIC...` instead of just `(new file)`. The fix is to use a non-greedy match that stops at the next field name: `r'^old_text:\\s*?(.+?)(?=\\nnew_text:|\\nfile:|\\Z)'`. Alternatively, I could match more precisely by capturing everything after the colon up to where `new_text:` or `file:` begins on the next line.\n\nActually, the simplest approach is to handle this in two passes: first extract the old_text value, then use string manipulation to remove it from the outer_content before matching new_text, so the patterns don't interfere with each other.","thinkingSignature":"5636be5f28274ac251673cdaf9acff604cb639834991acb37254d4aebac66f0a"},{"type":"text","text":"The LLM puts `old_text` and `new_text` on the same line with no newline between them. Let me fix the parser:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c6eab35mxbfe_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\parse_mutation.py","old_string":"# Extract old_text: from outer_content\nold_match = re.search(r'^old_text:\\s*(.+)$', outer_content, re.MULTILINE)\nold_text = old_match.group(1).strip() if old_match else \"\"","new_string":"# Extract old_text: from outer_content\n# Handle case where old_text and new_text are on the SAME LINE with no newline between them\n# e.g.: old_text: (new file)new_text: ...\nold_match = re.search(r'^old_text:\\s*(.+?)(?=\\nnew_text:|\\nfile:|\\Z)', outer_content, re.MULTILINE | re.DOTALL)\nold_text = old_match.group(1).strip() if old_match else \"\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":97626,"output":646,"cacheRead":13731,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112003,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774288192986}}
