{"type":"message","id":"7b9f5321","parentId":"4781d898","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:50:34.503Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Also need to handle the case where the new_text match on the SAME LINE captures more than it should. Let me also check the new_text extraction.\n\nLooking at the raw:```\nold_text: (new file)new_text: # TIC: Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\n```\n\nWhen I try to extract new_text starting from the \"new_text:\" after \"old_text: (new file)\", I need to find the right \"new_text:\" occurrence. The current code uses `re.search(r'^new_text:\\s*(.*)$', outer_content, re.MULTILINE)` which would match the first occurrence.\n\nBut the issue is that the code is trying to extract new_text by finding `new_text:` in `outer_content`, but the `nt_start_pos = new_text_match.end()` would be AFTER \"new_text: \" which starts on the same line as \"old_text:\". \n\n\nI need to look for the NEWLINE followed by \"new_text:\" or find the second occurrence of \"new_text:\" on that line. Tracing through what happens: `outer_content` contains everything between the triple backticks, so the regex `r'^new_text:\\s*(.*)$'` in MULTILINE mode should match at the start of the line \"new_text: # TIC...\", but the problem is that \"new_text:\" appears on the same line as \"old_text:\" with no newline between them, so the pattern isn't finding what I expect. The problem is that `re.search` with `^new_text:` in multiline mode finds the wrong match—the one embedded in the same line as `old_text: (new file)new_text: ...`. I need to locate the actual `new_text:` that starts a proper field, which should be on its own line or preceded by a newline. The cleanest approach is to search for `\\nnew_text:` and use its position to extract everything after it, then remove any nested backtick blocks from that extracted content. So I need to handle cases where `old_text:` and `new_text:` might be on the same line or different lines. Let me extract `old_text` first using the pattern that stops at the next field, then use that position to find `new_text:` which should come after it on the same line or a new line, and finally extract `file:` from wherever it appears.","thinkingSignature":"24ed75371c164a38eb7f7ef85ebb6ad365279fa8f51cc81ed53b8ee6eac7fa5a"},{"type":"text","text":"Also fix new_text extraction to handle same-line case:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_acxi0c66kqxm_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\parse_mutation.py","old_string":"# Extract new_text: from outer_content (multiline — until file: field or end)\nnew_text_match = re.search(r'^new_text:\\s*(.*)$', outer_content, re.MULTILINE)\nfile_match_in_outer = re.search(r'^file:\\s*(.+)$', outer_content, re.MULTILINE)\nif new_text_match:\n    nt_start_pos = new_text_match.end()\n    file_start_pos = file_match_in_outer.start() if file_match_in_outer else len(outer_content)\n    # Get raw new_text content (may contain nested triple backtick code blocks)\n    new_text_raw = outer_content[nt_start_pos:file_start_pos].rstrip()\n    # Remove nested triple-backtick code blocks (they're examples inside the text)\n    new_text = re.sub(r'```.*?```', '', new_text_raw, flags=re.DOTALL).strip()\nelse:\n    new_text = \"\"","new_string":"# Extract new_text: from outer_content (multiline — until file: field or end)\n# Two cases: new_text: on its own line, OR new_text: on same line as old_text:\n# Strategy: find the SECOND occurrence of \"new_text:\" OR find \"\\nnew_text:\"\n# Use the one that comes AFTER old_text in the content\nold_pos = outer_content.find(\"old_text:\")\n# Find the new_text: that comes AFTER old_text\nnt_search_start = old_pos + len(\"old_text:\") if old_pos >= 0 else 0\n# Look for \"\\nnew_text:\" (preferred — on its own line) or standalone \"new_text:\"\nnewline_nt = outer_content.find(\"\\nnew_text:\", nt_search_start)\nsame_line_nt = outer_content.find(\"new_text:\", nt_search_start)\n# Choose the one that comes first after old_text\nif newline_nt >= 0 and (same_line_nt < 0 or newline_nt < same_line_nt):\n    nt_marker = newline_nt + 1  # skip the newline, point at 'n' of \"new_text:\"\nelse:\n    nt_marker = same_line_nt if same_line_nt >= 0 else -1\n\nfile_match_in_outer = re.search(r'^file:\\s*(.+)$', outer_content, re.MULTILINE)\nif nt_marker >= 0:\n    # Find where new_text value ends — at \"file:\" or end of content\n    file_start = file_match_in_outer.start() if file_match_in_outer else len(outer_content)\n    # new_text value starts after \"new_text: \"\n    nt_value_start = nt_marker + len(\"new_text:\")\n    # Skip any newline right after \"new_text:\"\n    if nt_value_start < len(outer_content) and outer_content[nt_value_start] == \"\\n\":\n        nt_value_start += 1\n    elif nt_value_start < len(outer_content) and outer_content[nt_value_start] == \" \":\n        nt_value_start += 1\n    new_text_raw = outer_content[nt_value_start:file_start].rstrip()\n    # Remove nested triple-backtick code blocks\n    new_text = re.sub(r'```.*?```', '', new_text_raw, flags=re.DOTALL).strip()\nelse:\n    new_text = \"\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":97391,"output":1241,"cacheRead":13731,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112363,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774288210421}}
