nif mut_start < 0:\n    result = {\"old\": \"\", \"new\": \"\", \"file\": \"\"}\n    with open(os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \".mutation_parse_result.json\"), \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        json.dump(result, f, ensure_ascii=False)\n    print(\"ERROR: no MUTATION block\", file=sys.stderr)\n    sys.exit(1)\n\nblock = raw[mut_start:]","new_string":"mut_start = raw.find(\"### MUTATION\")\n# Fallback: if no header, look for the first triple-backtick block in the response\nif mut_start < 0:\n    tb = \"```\"\n    first_fence = raw.find(tb)\n    if first_fence >= 0:\n        # The MUTATION block starts at the first ```\n        mut_start = first_fence\n    else:\n        result = {\"old\": \"\", \"new\": \"\", \"file\": \"\"}\n        with open(os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \".mutation_parse_result.json\"), \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n            json.dump(result, f, ensure_ascii=False)\n        print(\"ERROR: no MUTATION block\", file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(1)\n\nblock = raw[mut_start:]"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":97580,"output":689,"cacheRead":13731,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112000,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774288323304}}
{"type":"message","id":"32e1c520","parentId":"aa213b8e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:52:18.640Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0ckev0yok39h_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\parse_mutation.py."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  11 with open(response_file, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n  12     raw = f.read()\n  13 \n  14 mut_start = raw.find(\"### MUTATION\")\n+ 15 # Fallback: if no header, look for the first triple-backtick block in the response\n  15 if mut_start < 0:\n- 16     result = {\"old\": \"\", \"new\": \"\", \"file\": \"\"}\n- 17     with open(os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \".mutation_parse_result.json\"), \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n- 18         json.dump(result, f, ensure_ascii=False)\n- 19     print(\"ERROR: no MUTATION block\", file=sys.stderr)\n- 20     sys.exit(1)\n+ 17     tb = \"```\"\n+ 18     first_fence = raw.find(tb)\n+ 19     if first_fence >= 0:\n+ 20         # The MUTATION block starts at the first ```\n+ 21         mut_start = first_fence\n+ 22     else:\n+ 23         result = {\"old\": \"\", \"new\": \"\", \"file\": \"\"}\n+ 24         with open(os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \".mutation_parse_result.json\"), \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n+ 25             json.dump(result, f, ensure_ascii=False)\n+ 26         print(\"ERROR: no MUTATION block\", file=sys.stderr)\n+ 27         sys.exit(1)\n  21 \n  22 block = raw[mut_start:]\n  23 \n  24 # Strategy:\n     ...","firstChangedLine":15},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774288338607}}
{"type":"message","id":"f5c6d2c7","parentId":"32e1c520","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:52:36.158Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, but the `block` would start at the first triple backtick. The triple backtick would be the opening fence. But then when I look for the `old_text:` inside the block... the block starts at the triple backtick. So the content would be `\\`\\`\\`old_text:...`. But the triple backtick is part of the fence, not the content. I need to skip past the opening fence.\n\nLet me trace through:\n- `block = raw[mut_start:]` = starts at the first backtick of the opening fence\n- `tb_positions` finds all triple backticks in `block`\n\n\n- `outer_content = block[first_tb + 3:last_tb]` = content between the first and last triple backtick\n\nThat should work correctly. The opening fence sits at the start of `block`, and `tb_positions[0]` points to index 0 where the triple backtick begins, so extracting from position 3 onward correctly skips past that opening fence marker.\n\nFor the closing fence, `block[last_tb + 3:]` would grab everything after the last triple backtick, which gives us the content that comes after the MUTATION block ends. But I need to verify what `block` actually contains at this point—it might not be structured the way I'm assuming if the first triple backtick isn't actually the opening fence.\n\nLooking at the actual LLM output, the triple backtick appears after the text \"INVARIANT:\" without any MUTATION header before it. So the file content would be the response body followed by the code block with old_text, new_text, and file fields inside it.\n\nWhen I search for the first triple backtick, that gives me the start of the code block. I extract the outer content between the first and last triple backticks, which would contain just the field lines. That should work, but I need to verify the closing fence logic isn't grabbing too much. I see the issue now—the closing fence extraction is pulling in everything after the last triple backtick, which includes the `file:` line and the trailing fence, so I need to adjust where the slice ends to avoid capturing that extra content.","thinkingSignature":"307a9bf11d00ac9c1978bc5794bfd4ae661d07c936f1210e2e592c48010bd9e1"},{"type":"text","text":"Also need to fix the `after_close` to NOT include the closing fence itself:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_e7jyy3r1qte9_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\parse_mutation.py","oldString":"    outer_content = block[first_tb + 3:last_tb]  # between first and last fences\n    after_close = block[last_tb + 3:]  # after closing fence","new_string":"    outer_content = block[first_tb + 3:last_tb]  # between first and last fences (opening fence skipped)\n    after_close = block[last_tb + 3:]  # content after closing fence (skip the fence chars)"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":97586,"output":623,"cacheRead":13731,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":111940,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774288338651}}
