{"type":"message","id":"f923659d","parentId":"cacfb880","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:52:43.327Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, it says Missing required parameter: oldText. That's weird because I'm not trying to use oldText. Let me check what happened.\n\nOh wait, I think the edit tool is confused. Let me re-read the file to see the current state.","thinkingSignature":"caf01fc234762d01a5f5cd5b69be2d87b604d0bf2da183e95b77d4b582041b1b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_no0cjyoug65w_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\parse_mutation.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":97817,"output":93,"cacheRead":13731,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":111641,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774288356229}}
{"type":"message","id":"5cebaa59","parentId":"f923659d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:52:43.376Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_no0cjyoug65w_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nparse_mutation.py — Robust mutation field extractor\nHandles the complex case where:\n  - old_text/new_text are in a single-backtick inline region\n  - triple backticks are NESTED inside new_text as a code example\n  - file: comes after the triple-backtick block\n\"\"\"\nimport sys, re, os, json\n\nresponse_file = sys.argv[1] if len(sys.argv) > 1 else os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \".llm_response.txt\")\nwith open(response_file, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n    raw = f.read()\n\nmut_start = raw.find(\"### MUTATION\")\n# Fallback: if no header, look for the first triple-backtick block in the response\nif mut_start < 0:\n    tb = \"```\"\n    first_fence = raw.find(tb)\n    if first_fence >= 0:\n        # The MUTATION block starts at the first ```\n        mut_start = first_fence\n    else:\n        result = {\"old\": \"\", \"new\": \"\", \"file\": \"\"}\n        with open(os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \".mutation_parse_result.json\"), \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n            json.dump(result, f, ensure_ascii=False)\n        print(\"ERROR: no MUTATION block\", file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(1)\n\nblock = raw[mut_start:]\n\n# Strategy:\n# Find all triple backtick (```) positions. There are two cases:\n# Case 1 (single-backtick outer): old_text/new_text before first ```, file: after last ```\n# Case 2 (triple-backtick outer): content between first and last ```, file: after last ```\n# Case 3 (no fences): whole block is content\n\ntb = \"```\"\ntb_positions = []\nsearch_from = 0\nwhile True:\n    p = block.find(tb, search_from)\n    if p == -1:\n        break\n    tb_positions.append(p)\n    search_from = p + 3\n\nif len(tb_positions) >= 2:\n    # There are nested triple backtick fences\n    # Content is between the FIRST and LAST ``` (outer block)\n    # The fences at tb_positions[0] and tb_positions[-1] are the outer wrapper\n    first_tb = tb_positions[0]\n    last_tb = tb_positions[-1]\n    outer_content = block[first_tb + 3:last_tb]  # between first and last fences\n    after_close = block[last_tb + 3:]  # after closing fence\nelif len(tb_positions) == 1:\n    # Only one fence — can't determine outer block\n    outer_content = block\n    after_close = \"\"\nelse:\n    # No fences — whole block is the content\n    outer_content = block\n    after_close = \"\"\n\n# Extract old_text: from outer_content\n# Handle case where old_text and new_text are on the SAME LINE with no newline between them\n# e.g.: old_text: (new file)new_text: ...\nold_match = re.search(r'^old_text:\\s*(.+?)(?=\\nnew_text:|\\nfile:|\\Z)', outer_content, re.MULTILINE | re.DOTALL)\nold_text = old_match.group(1).strip() if old_match else \"\"\n\n# Extract new_text: from outer_content (multiline — until file: field or end)\n# Two cases: new_text: on its own line, OR new_text: on same line as old_text:\n# Strategy: find the SECOND occurrence of \"new_text:\" OR find \"\\nnew_text:\"\n# Use the one that comes AFTER old_text in the content\nold_pos = outer_content.find(\"old_text:\")\n# Find the new_text: that comes AFTER old_text\nnt_search_start = old_pos + len(\"old_text:\") if old_pos >= 0 else 0\n# Look for \"\\nnew_text:\" (preferred — on its own line) or standalone \"new_text:\"\nnewline_nt = outer_content.find(\"\\nnew_text:\", nt_search_start)\nsame_line_nt = outer_content.find(\"new_text:\", nt_search_start)\n# Choose the one that comes first after old_text\nif newline_nt >= 0 and (same_line_nt < 0 or newline_nt < same_line_nt):\n    nt_marker = newline_nt + 1  # skip the newline, point at 'n' of \"new_text:\"\nelse:\n    nt_marker = same_line_nt if same_line_nt >= 0 else -1\n\nfile_match_in_outer = re.search(r'^file:\\s*(.+)$', outer_content, re.MULTILINE)\nif nt_marker >= 0:\n    # Find where new_text value ends — at \"file:\" or end of content\n    file_start = file_match_in_outer.start() if file_match_in_outer else len(outer_content)\n    # new_text value starts after \"new_text: \"\n    nt_value_start = nt_marker + len(\"new_text:\")\n    # Skip any newline right after \"new_text:\"\n    if nt_value_start < len(outer_content) and outer_content[nt_value_start] == \"\\n\":\n        nt_value_start += 1\n    elif nt_value_start < len(outer_content) and outer_content[nt_value_start] == \" \":\n        nt_value_start += 1\n    new_text_raw = outer_content[nt_value_start:file_start].rstrip()\n    # Remove nested triple-backtick code blocks\n    new_text = re.sub(r'```.*?```', '', new_text_raw, flags=re.DOTALL).strip()\nelse:\n    new_text = \"\"\n\n# Extract file: from after_close (after the outer triple backtick block)\nfile_match = re.search(r'^file:\\s*(.+)$', after_close, re.MULTILINE)\nfile_text = file_match.group(1).strip() if file_match else \"\"\n\n# Fallback: search the whole block for file:\nif not file_text:\n    file_match2 = re.search(r'^file:\\s*(.+)', block, re.MULTILINE)\n    file_text = file_match2.group(1).strip() if file_match2 else \"\"\n\nprint(f\"DEBUG: old={repr(old_text[:40] if old_text else '')}\", file=sys.stderr)\nprint(f\"DEBUG: new_text len={len(new_text)}, starts={repr(new_text[:60] if new_text else '')}\", file=sys.stderr)\nprint(f\"DEBUG: file={repr(file_text)}\", file=sys.stderr)\n\nresult = {\"old\": old_text, \"new\": new_text, \"file\": file_text}\nresult_file = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \".mutation_parse_result.json\")\nwith open(result_file, \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n    json.dump(result, f, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2)\nprint(f\"Result written to {result_file}\", file=sys.stderr)\nsys.stdout.write(\"OK\")\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774288363353}}
{"type":"message","id":"9f54dc0f","parentId":"5cebaa59","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:53:00.198Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The file already has the fix I wanted to apply (the edit must have gone through earlier but the error message was wrong). The code looks correct. The issue now is that the outer_content when there's no `### MUTATION` header starts at the first backtick of the triple fence. But then `block[first_tb + 3:last_tb]` — if `first_tb` is at position 0 (because the block starts with ```), then `block[3:last_tb]` is the content between the opening and closing fences.\n\nBut wait — the triple backtick at the start is `block[0:3] = '```'`. \n\nSo when I extract `block[3:last_tb]`, I'm getting the content between the opening and closing fences, which is correct. But then for `after_close`, I need to think through what the indices actually represent — the block starts with the opening fence at 0-2, the content runs from 3 to last_tb-1, and the closing fence sits at last_tb through last_tb+2, so `after_close` should start at last_tb+3 and grab everything that follows, which would be the `file:` line.\n\nLooking at the actual response content, I can see the file path appears after the closing fence with a newline, so the slicing is working as intended — I just confirmed the logic checks out and should run the test.","thinkingSignature":"3cdfcfd3c12cab081c4e63c38419c64e49ba78bb7d4825729aefc0ef4c300956"},{"type":"text","text":"The parser looks correct now. Run the pulse:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_17vjvr37icgc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox; powershell -File pulse.ps1 2>&1","yieldMs":250000,"timeout":300}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":98202,"output":377,"cacheRead":13731,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112310,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"