{"type":"message","id":"584efe7f","parentId":"31abd985","timestamp":"2026-03-23T17:54:48.871Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is at line 75. The condition checks `$current.Length -eq 0 -or $current -notmatch [regex]::Escape($oldText)`. But if `$oldText` is empty string, `[regex]::Escape(\"\")` returns \"\" and `$current -notmatch \"\"` is ALWAYS true (matching empty string against anything matches). So the condition should fail and we should continue to Replace. Wait...\n\nActually, the issue might be different. Let me trace through what happens:1. Mutation has `old_text: (new file)` → parsed as `oldText = \"(new file)\"`2. In pulse.ps1, we check `if ($oldLine -and $fileLine -and $newText)` → all three are non-empty3. \n\nSo the mutation gets saved with `oldText = \"(new file)\"`. When the file already exists and we hit the `[NEW_FILE]` block, we move it to applied and continue, which means that mutation is done. But then we loop through the rest of the mutations in the directory, and that's where we hit another mutation with `$oldText = \"\"`.\n\nIf `$oldText` is empty, then `$current -notmatch [regex]::Escape(\"\")` becomes `$current -notmatch \"\"`, which is always false since an empty string matches anywhere. So the condition `$current.Length -eq 0 -or (-not $oldText) -or $current -notmatch [regex]::Escape($oldText)` evaluates to `False or True or False = True`, which means we reject it with \"old text not found\". But we're still hitting a Replace call with an empty string somewhere, so I need to add an explicit check to reject mutations where `$oldText` is empty before we ever get to the Replace call. oldText is empty BEFORE calling Replace. Let me add a guard at the Replace line itself:","thinkingSignature":"89c70e952d3ede87f8fe1c6a58c1ddf81957b1efb0cfc0d130b2d143f064f086"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8wdj2mmaw8fb_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1