{"type":"message","id":"faeb38b1","parentId":"69fb7ba3","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:37:35.653Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to:\n1. Start the botshoppebot service as a background process\n2. Update OpenClaw's cron jobs to POST to `http://127.0.0.1:4892/notify` instead of using the announce delivery\n\nBut wait - the cron jobs run in the OpenClaw gateway's isolated session, which might not have access to localhost. Actually, since the cron jobs run as isolated agent sessions on the same machine, they should be able to reach localhost:4892.\n\nLet me start the botshoppebot service first.","thinkingSignature":"8cea50ed1d210f894fb1d4598ea1d27cf5453c680552bcb6d2638d9b676f2cd0"},{"type":"text","text":"\nNow start it as a background process and update OpenClaw's crons to POST notifications:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r8lfiz85ijpx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace; Start-Process -FilePath python -ArgumentList \"botshoppebot_service.py\" -WindowStyle Hidden; Start-Sleep -Seconds 2; curl -s -X POST \"http://127.0.0.1:4892/notify\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d \"{\\\"text\\\":\\\"✅ botshoppebot service started\\\"}\" 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":111716,"output":265,"cacheRead":13774,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":125755,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774294648725}}
