{"type":"message","id":"f6bb73b8","parentId":"57825df8","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:39:39.261Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Same result. Let me try using `Start-Process` with the `-PassThru` flag and see if it has `HasExited=True` immediately.Actually, I think the issue might be that when running from PowerShell with background=true, the process is being created but immediately getting an error. Let me try running it differently.\n\nActually wait - when I use `exec` with `background=true`, the session immediately returns with \"Exec failed (code 1)\". Let me check what's actually happening. Maybe the Python process is failing because it can't find `socketserver`.Actually, I think the problem is that `socketserver.TCPServer` is blocking the thread. \n\nEven with `daemon=True` on the thread, the `serve_forever()` call is probably hanging and preventing the script from exiting. I should switch to `ThreadingTCPServer` instead, which handles each request in its own thread so the main thread can continue.","thinkingSignature":"e37e155e12aa135bd7de80e7a26e30b40620ca9c76c2db00cf79b3e5397c0cda"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6d4witmh0ga0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace; python -c \"\nimport socketserver\nprint('socketserver OK')\nprint(dir(socketserver))\n\" 2>&1","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":115613,"output":271,"cacheRead":13774,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":129658,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774294770597}}
