{"type":"message","id":"9de7d2fc","parentId":"a9ea012b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:41:07.312Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No Python process running on port 4892. The background session timed out because the OpenClaw exec `background=true` sessions have a default timeout. Let me try running it with a proper background approach - using `Start-Process` with `-PassThru`.Actually, wait. Let me re-read the OpenClaw exec documentation. When `background=true`, the session is created and the command runs in the background, but it still seems to time out. The background sessions seem to have a much shorter lifetime than expected.\n\nLet me try a completely different approach: use Task Scheduler to run the bot as a persistent background task. Or use `nssm` to run it as a Windows service.Actually, the simplest approach for persistent background on Windows that works: use `Start-Process` with `-PassThru` and then immediately return. \n\nThe process should keep running even after the shell exits since Windows doesn't kill child processes when their parent terminates. But the `HasExited=True` status is concerning—that shouldn't happen if the process is supposed to persist. Let me try running it as a detached process with proper stdin/stdout redirection instead.","thinkingSignature":"85b64cedd26e0dd377c08335ebdacf6df7109eba9c9b57cdb3674f5d878c812a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_281ccf2eiox8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$proc = Start-Process -FilePath python -ArgumentList \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\botshoppebot_service.py\" -PassThru -WindowStyle Hidden -RedirectStandardOutput \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\botshoppebot_out.log\" -RedirectStandardError \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\botshoppebot_err.log\"; Start-Sleep -Seconds 3; Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\botshoppebot_err.log\" -Raw -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue; Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.opencla