{"type":"message","id":"fd2a6a2a","parentId":"d49e5d57","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:45:37.624Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so Python is 64-bit. Let me try a completely different approach. Since the OpenClaw exec with `background=true` DID work (the HTTP server was responding to requests), let me just use that. I need to increase the timeout to a very large value so the session doesn't kill the process.Actually, wait. Looking back at the earlier results - the session `dawn-ridge` was started with `timeout: 2500` seconds and completed (exit code 0) after about 21 minutes. The background exec sessions seem to time out normally.\n\nThe key insight: when I ran `python botshoppebot_service.py` with `background=true` and a very large timeout, the process started and was running. The issue was that when the exec tool's timeout fired, it killed the background process too.\n \nInstead of trying to keep the background process alive indefinitely, I'll set up a Scheduled Task to run the script at system startup - that way the bot starts automatically without relying on an exec session staying alive.","thinkingSignature":"6086744bf586ec66b15fa8bc4b58ecb5e1e4ee268a9616202505bad4b0656f9b"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me try running it via Task Scheduler with the current user logged on:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_eqnxw77bpsly_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$py = (Get-Command python).Source; $action = New-ScheduledTaskAction -Execute $py -Argument \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\botshoppebot_simple.py\" -WorkingDirectory \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\"; $principal = New-ScheduledTaskPrincipal -UserId $env:USERNAME -LogonType Interactive -RunLevel Highest; $settings = New-ScheduledTaskSettingsSet -AllowStartIfOnBatteries -DontStopIfGoingOnBatteries -StartWhenAvailable; $task = Register-ScheduledTask -TaskName \"botshoppebot\" -Action $action -Principal $principal -Settings $settings -Force 2>&1; Start-ScheduledTask -TaskName \"botshoppebot\" 2>&1; Get-ScheduledTask -TaskName \"botshoppebot\" | Select-Object State; Start-Sleep -Seconds 3; curl -s -X POST \"http://127.0.0.1:4892/notify\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d \"{\\\"text\\\":\\\"ping from curl\\\"}\"","timeout":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":124159,"output":498,"cacheRead":13774,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":138431,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774295124316}}
