{"type":"message","id":"2844cd22","parentId":"88455e49","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:46:12.600Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The system logs show that botshoppebot is running and trying to bind to port 4892, but getting an error 457 - `OSError: [WinError 457] The specified network address is not valid`. This is `server_bind()` failing, which means the port is already in use OR the address is invalid.\n\nWait - the earlier sessions (gentle-c, wild-pra, mellow-r) are from the earlier polling attempts. The sessions are actually running and the errors are about port binding.\n\nBut looking at the system message - this shows exec failures for previous sessions. The port 4892 binding error means something else is already on that port, OR the service is actually trying to run multiple instances.\n\n\nActually, looking more carefully - these are old session failures, not current ones. The real issue is that port 4892 is already bound by something, so I need to kill whatever's using it and start fresh.","thinkingSignature":"4b1b96dcdcb81c34c008bd70df4a8c79fad04d291cb4a4bbf6e6b914155ad4df"},{"type":"text","text":"The system logs show port 4892 is already bound — an earlier session is still holding it. Let me kill the old processes and restart:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_82itbq9wnp1v_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Process -Name python | Where-Object { $_.CommandLine -match \"botshoppebot|4892\" } | Select-Object Id; netstat -ano | Select-String \":4892\" 2>$null","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":302,"cacheRead":13774,"cacheWrite":118467,"totalTokens":132586,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774295158974}}
