{"type":"message","id":"ffb042e9","parentId":"af932411","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:47:29.101Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It's getting stuck at `server_forever()`. The previous attempts that show as exited - they're zombie processes from Task Scheduler that are holding the port but not actually accepting connections.\n\nThe issue is: when Task Scheduler starts the process, it runs in session 0 (system session) as a different user. My `Start-Process` runs in the desktop session. Both are running, but only one can bind the port.\n\nThe real problem: the Task Scheduler processes (17304, 16084) are still actually running somehow despite `Get-Process` not finding them. They're orphaned session-0 processes.\n\nActually wait - the `netstat` showed these as holding the port. But `Get-Process` didn't find them by that ID. \n\nThose PIDs might be gone by now, so the port should be free. Let me check what actually happens when I try to bind to it again.","thinkingSignature":"5fe6801be24b4a868a52faecd4feb3fd07eee35c509a245f953e753a1c9b0b8f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3tjw04d7imah_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace; python -c \"\nfrom socketserver import ThreadingTCPServer\nclass H:\n    def do_POST(self): self.send_response(200); self.end_headers(); self.wfile.write(b'OK')\n    def log_message(self, *a): pass\nsrv = ThreadingTCPServer(('127.0.0.1', 4892), type('H',(H,),{}))\nsrv.allow_reuse_address = True\nprint('bind OK')\nsrv.server_close()\nprint('closed OK')\n\" 2>&1","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":120139,"output":340,"cacheRead":13774,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":134253,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774295239413}}
