{"type":"message","id":"e5998660","parentId":"69ea6b27","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:47:39.619Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so port 4892 is actually free now (no zombie processes). The issue is that when I `Start-Process` a Python script, it immediately exits. This might be because of how the process is being started. Let me try a different approach.\n\nLet me just run it with `cmd /c start` to run in a new window, or use `Start-Process` without `-PassThru` and check if it's running differently.\n\nActually, I realize I should just spawn it as a proper background job using PowerShell's `Start-Job` with the `-FilePath` parameter, which explicitly runs the script in a background job context.\n\nLet me also check: maybe the issue is that the Scheduled Task is causing issues - when the task runs in session 0, it might be setting some state that persists even after the task dies.","thinkingSignature":"f6e8aaf88f8f8a3a2d1b56b0af534add9a39afa22c65a595e57f4dd49f8fb067"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nxxj0jepq7t1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Unregister-ScheduledTask -TaskName \"botshoppebot\" -Confirm:$false -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue; Unregister-ScheduledTask -TaskName \"botshoppebot_debug\" -Confirm:$false -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue; Start-Sleep -Seconds 2; cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace; Start-Job -Name botshoppebot -FilePath \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\botshoppebot_simple.py\" -InitializationScript $null 2>&1 | Select-Object Id, State, HasMoreData","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":120504,"output":332,"cacheRead":13774,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":134610,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774295249937}}
