{"type":"message","id":"a3c370cb","parentId":"ed28fe9c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:48:00.038Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `timeout` command ran the Python script for 3 seconds but produced no output. This is suspicious. It means either:\n1. The script ran fine for 3 seconds and timeout killed it (expected)\n2. The script failed to start at all\n\nBut the `timeout` output shows no Python errors, no \"EXIT\" echo. This means the `timeout` command itself might not be passing through correctly. Let me try a simpler test.\n\nWait - maybe the issue is that the script is blocking in the `serve_forever()` call and timeout kills it after 3 seconds, which is expected behavior. But why did the `Start-Job` and `Start-Process` show `HasExited: True` almost immediately?","thinkingSignature":"fd80dd8f2218e0758fbb419e5bf3157fd3f82114518b6005ef142dbd8653de8a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4m09hlursxmh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace; powershell -Command \"Start-Job -Name btest -ScriptBlock { cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace; python botshoppebot_simple.py }; Start-Sleep -Seconds 3; Get-Job -Name btest | Select-Object Id,State,HasMoreData; Receive-Job -Name btest -Keep\" 2>&1","yieldMs":8000,"timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":121004,"output":288,"cacheRead":13774,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":135066,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774295271106}}
