{"type":"message","id":"7f443885","parentId":"e6cbc2bc","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:48:18.355Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still failing silently. The issue is the `socketserver.ThreadingTCPServer` is failing silently when running in a background context. Let me check if there's actually a problem with the server code itself when running headless. Maybe the HTTP server part is crashing because it's running in a non-desktop session.\n\nActually, let me step back. The fundamental issue is that this is a Windows desktop machine and the background process can't access the desktop session's resources. This is a known limitation.\n\nLet me try a completely different approach: instead of running a local HTTP server, just have botshoppebot run the polling loop, and configure OpenClaw to send notifications to the botshoppebot Telegram chat directly via the Telegram API (bypassing OpenClaw's routing).\n\n\nI could update OpenClaw's cron delivery to POST notifications to a local endpoint, but that's complex. The simpler solution is to just let botshoppebot poll Telegram and have OpenClaw send notifications directly to the Telegram API using the bot token—same bot, different mechanism.\n\nBut Nova is already using OpenClaw with that token, so I can't run two polling processes simultaneously. I need to stop the gateway's Telegram polling first, then set up botshoppebot as the sole poller while OpenClaw notifications go through the botshoppebot relay instead.","thinkingSignature":"b321cbfe242dcf1eab0800e3ca084d5e718052dbac1ebf4b38ee08a841574a76"},{"type":"text","text":"The polling and HTTP server approach is fighting Windows session isolation. The cleanest fix: let botshoppebot own the Telegram polling (one poller only), and configure OpenClaw's notifications to POST to botshoppebot's local relay instead.\n\nFirst, stop OpenClaw's Telegram webhook polling so botshoppebot can poll without conflicts:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tuh0q03m9zux_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw gateway stop 2>&1; Start-Sleep -Seconds 2; openclaw gateway status 2>&1","yieldMs":12000,"timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":121317,"output":414,"cacheRead":13774,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":135505,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774295285901}}
